author%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225368%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jonathan%20Haidt%20at%2092NY%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20on%20May%2005%2C%202026%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a214849b4fb977f3598446f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223579%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENYU%20professor%20Jonathan%20Haidt%20said%20AI%20toys%20are%20always%20available%20and%20could%20compromise%20children's%20relationships%20with%20their%20parents.%3Cp%3EDia%20Dipasupil%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ELeading%20social%20psychologist%20Jonathan%20Haidt%20warned%20about%20the%20impact%20of%20AI%20toys%20in%20a%20TED%20Talk.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EChildren%20risk%20becoming%20attached%20to%20AI%20companions%20if%20they%20bond%20with%20them%2C%20he%20said.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20could%20weaken%20children's%20bonds%20with%20their%20parents%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EJonathan%20Haidt%2C%20the%20NYU%20Stern%20School%20of%20Business%20professor%20whose%20book%20%26quot%3BThe%20Anxious%20Generation%26quot%3B%20helped%20spark%20a%20global%20debate%20about%20the%20impact%20of%20smartphones%20and%20social%20media%20on%20young%20people's%20mental%20health%2C%20has%20a%20new%20concern%3A%20AI%20toys%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Edesigned%20for%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20at%20a%20recent%20TED%20Talk%2C%20Haidt%20said%20that%20the%20rapidly%20growing%20market%20for%20AI-powered%20toys%20and%20chatbots%20could%20interfere%20with%20children's%20relationships%20with%20their%20parents%20by%20becoming%20emotional%20attachment%20figures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20seeing%20a%20booming%20AI%20toy%20market.%20Chatbots%20are%20being%20put%20into%20dolls%20and%20teddy%20bears%2C%26quot%3B%20Haidt%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20he%20didn't%20single%20out%20specific%20products%2C%20a%20growing%20category%20of%20AI-powered%20toys%20and%20companions%20has%20emerged%20over%20the%20last%20couple%20of%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExamples%20include%20Moxie%2C%20an%20AI-powered%20social%20robot%20designed%20to%20be%20children's%20friend%2C%20tutor%2C%20and%20mentor%2C%20as%20well%20as%20chatbot-enabled%20dolls%20and%20teddy%20bears%20developed%20by%20startups%20like%20Curio.%20Toy%20giant%20Mattel%20has%20also%20partnered%20with%20OpenAI%20to%20explore%20AI-powered%20products%2C%20showing%20how%20quickly%20the%20category%20is%20evolving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarket%20research%20firm%20Grand%20View%20Research%20estimates%20that%20the%20global%20smart%20toy%20market%2C%20including%20AI%20toys%2C%20will%20grow%20from%20%2414.39%20billion%20in%202025%20to%20%2444%20billion%20by%202033.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsmartphones-gen-z-creativity-attention-jonathan-haidt-anxious-generation-careers-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esocial%20psychologist%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20these%20products%20are%20designed%20to%20be%20highly%20responsive%20to%20children%2C%20offering%20comfort%2C%20conversation%2C%20and%20companionship%20whenever%20they're%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20constant%20availability%20could%20make%20them%20especially%20appealing%20to%20young%20users.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20chatbots%20are%20super%20responsive%20to%20the%20child.%20They're%20always%20there%20to%20offer%20comfort%2C%20to%20be%20there%20for%20the%20child%20%E2%80%94%20and%20of%20course%2C%20the%20parents%20are%20often%20busy%2C%26quot%3B%20Haidt%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222722322c-0868-4e05-9ebd-5f79c6fab67b%5C%22%3EThe%20danger%20of%20artificial%20relationships%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHaidt's%20warning%20comes%20as%20AI%20companions%20are%20already%20reshaping%20people's%20social%20and%20romantic%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsers%20say%20they've%20fallen%20in%20love%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdating-ai-companion-replika-vs-human-pros-cons-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20partners%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20relied%20on%20chatbots%20for%20daily%20companionship%2C%20and%20even%20feared%20losing%20the%20relationships%20they've%20formed%20with%20virtual%20companions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaidt's%20concern%2C%20however%2C%20centers%20on%20how%20children%20form%20attachments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYoung%20children%20naturally%20gravitate%20toward%20people%20who%20consistently%20respond%20to%20their%20needs%2C%20he%20said.%20If%20AI%20companions%20become%20more%20reliably%20responsive%20than%20parents%2C%20they%20could%20begin%20to%20occupy%20an%20unhealthy%20role%20in%20a%20child's%20emotional%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20chatbot%20is%20super%20responsive%20while%20the%20parents%20aren't%20as%20responsive%2C%20the%20child's%20attachment%20system%2C%20which%20is%20looking%20for%20who%20in%20my%20environment%20is%20the%20person%20who%20responds%20to%20me%2C%20may%20well%20imprint%20or%20focus%20on%20the%20chatbot%2C%20which%20is%20going%20to%20compromise%20their%20relationship%20with%20their%20own%20parents%2C%26quot%3B%20Haidt%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fb657288-94c5-4867-b473-29273109c8f9%5C%22%3ETechno-skeptic%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20warning%20is%20part%20of%20a%20broader%20argument%20Haidt%20has%20been%20making%20about%20what%20he%20calls%20%26quot%3Btechno-skepticism.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esociety%20moved%20too%20quickly%20in%20allowing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-tech-execs-balance-ai-screentime-social-media-limits-kids-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esocial%20media%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20shape%20children's%20social%20lives%20and%20educational%20technology%20companies%20to%20reshape%20classrooms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20let%20social%20media%20companies%20take%20over%20our%20kids'%20social%20lives%2C%20and%20they've%20harmed%20our%20kids'%20social%20lives%20and%20their%20mental%20health%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20let%20EdTech%20companies%20take%20over%20our%20kids'%20schools%2C%20and%20they%20appear%20to%20be%20doing%20more%20harm%20than%20good.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20he%20said%2C%20AI%20companies%20are%20targeting%20an%20even%20more%20intimate%20part%20of%20childhood%3A%20relationships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAI%20companies%20are%20coming%20for%20their%20relationships%2C%20to%20be%20their%20friends%2C%20their%20therapists%2C%26quot%3B%20Haidt%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20could%20go%20wrong%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20he%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-therapy-risks-benefits-boundaries-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20therapists%3C%2Fa%3E%20may%20eventually%20have%20a%20role%2C%20he%20said%20that%20companies%20should%20not%20be%20allowed%20to%20deploy%20emotionally%20persuasive%20AI%20products%20to%20children%20without%20years%20of%20safety%20testing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGive%20them%20nothing%20that%20conveys%20that%20it%20understands%20the%20child%20or%20that%20it%20cares%2C%26quot%3B%20Haidt%20said.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20it%20doesn't.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-toys-could-weaken-parent-child-bond-anxious-generation-author-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780576024000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a21485ab4fb977f35984470%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-toys-could-weaken-parent-child-bond-anxious-generation-author-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22AI%20toys%20could%20compromise%20children's%20relationships%20with%20their%20parents%2C%20NYU%20professor%20Jonathan%20Haidt%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tspirlet%40insider.com%20(Thibault%20Spirlet)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22UAE%20announces%20public%20holiday%20for%20Islamic%20New%20Year%2C%20three-day%20weekend%20for%20employees%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780575781000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-131507142%2Cimgsize-336952.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fuae-announces-public-holiday-for-islamic-new-year-three-day-weekend-for-employees%2Farticleshow%2F131506367.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F131506367.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20World%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fuae-announces-public-holiday-for-islamic-new-year-three-day-weekend-for-employees%2Farticleshow%2F131506367.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fuae-announces-public-holiday-for-islamic-new-year-three-day-weekend-for-employees%2Famp_articleshow%2F131506367.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fuae-announces-public-holiday-for-islamic-new-year-three-day-weekend-for-employees%2Famp_articleshow%2F131506367.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20moved%20from%20the%20US%20to%20Denmark.%20It%20forced%20me%20to%20rethink%20my%20parenting.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223852%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Woman%20posing%20for%20photo%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a0c805df246b392afc7b6eb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222889%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20moved%20from%20the%20US%20to%20Denmark.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Rebekah%20Joy%20Portraits%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ELiving%20in%20Denmark%20changed%20how%20I%20think%20about%20parenting%20and%20independence.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI%20realized%20much%20of%20my%20parenting%20anxiety%20came%20from%20fear%20of%20falling%20behind.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDanish%20culture%20taught%20me%20to%20trust%20my%20child%20more%20and%20control%20less.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20looked%20at%20my%20Danish%20husband's%20social%20media%2C%20you%20wouldn't%20know%20he%20is%20a%20parent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20no%20monthly%20updates%20about%20our%203-year-old%20son%2C%20Aksel%2C%20no%20sentimental%20captions%20about%20milestones%2C%20and%20no%20proof%20that%20he%20is%20involved%20in%20family%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20truth%20is%2C%20he%20is%20an%20incredible%20father.%20He%20just%20doesn't%20feel%20the%20need%20to%20narrate%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20moved%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprofessional-matchmaker-how-i-found-love-soulmate-while-solo-traveling-2020-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20to%20Denmark%3C%2Fa%3E%20eight%20years%20ago%20for%20love%2C%20I%20barely%20noticed%20that%20difference.%20But%20after%20becoming%20a%20mother%20in%20Copenhagen%2C%20I%20started%20to%20see%20how%20much%20of%20the%20parenting%20culture%20I%20had%20absorbed%20in%20America%20was%20about%20proof%3A%20proof%20I%20was%20trying%20hard%20enough%2C%20sacrificing%20enough%2C%20and%20doing%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Denmark%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-parenting-in-denmark-taught-me-about-raising-kids-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eparenting%20feels%20less%20curated%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20less%20dependent%20on%20public%20approval.%20While%20that%20does%20not%20mean%20love%20is%20absent%20or%20less%20intense%2C%20it%20feels%20different%20from%20the%20constant%20social%20media%20comparisons%20around%20motherhood%20that%20seem%20to%20dominate%20my%20American%20social%20media%20feed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20longer%20I%20parent%20here%2C%20the%20more%20I%20realize%20that%20becoming%20a%20%26quot%3Bgood%20parent%2C%26quot%3B%20at%20least%20for%20me%2C%20has%20meant%20unlearning%20instincts%20I%20did%20not%20even%20know%20I%20had%20absorbed%3A%20the%20urge%20to%20manage%2C%20document%2C%20and%20enrich%20every%20aspect%20of%20my%20child's%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22de013f14-f8d4-4d4c-bc83-d33384ef6e32%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFatherhood%20looks%20different%20here%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20having%20Aksel%2C%20I%2C%20of%20course%2C%20believed%20in%20gender%20equality.%20However%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-it-really-means-to-be-a-mother-today-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emotherhood%20taught%20me%3C%2Fa%3E%20how%20swiftly%20those%20ideals%20can%20collapse%20after%20having%20a%20baby%2C%20especially%20for%20women%20raised%20in%20cultures%20where%20maternal%20love%20seems%20measured%20by%20the%20burdens%20they%20shoulder%20without%20complaint%20(American%20trends%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrad-wife-on-tiktok-shares-idyllic-lifestyle-risks-money-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETikTok%20tradwives%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20exacerbate%20this).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDenmark%20challenged%20what%20I%20had%20accepted%20as%20normal%20because%2C%20here%2C%20fathers%20aren't%20usually%20applauded%20for%20the%20bare%20minimum.%20In%20many%20Danish%20families%2C%20including%20my%20own%2C%20dads%20are%20expected%20to%20be%20full%20parents%2C%20not%20assistants%20to%20motherhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDenmark's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdenmark-parent-benefits-american-free-childcare-maternity-leave-postpartum-care-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eparental%20leave%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%20reflects%20that%20expectation%2C%20too.%20Under%20the%20latest%20parental%20leave%20model%2C%20rolled%20out%20in%20October%202022%2C%20leave%20is%20divided%20more%20evenly%20between%20genders%2C%20with%20each%20parent%20receiving%20a%20portion%20that%20cannot%20be%20transferred%20to%20the%20other.%20All%20over%20Copenhagen%2C%20you'll%20see%20dads%20pushing%20strollers%2C%20coffees%20in%20hand%2C%20often%20walking%20with%20other%20fathers%20on%20leave.%20This%20isn't%20a%20novelty%3B%20it's%20just%20parenting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20makes%20shared%20caregiving%20more%20explicit%20than%20the%20model%20I%20grew%20up%20with%20in%20the%20US.%20My%20mother%2C%20an%20elementary%20school%20teacher%2C%20had%20two%20weeks%20off%20after%20I%20was%20born.%20My%20father%2C%20a%20teacher%20at%20the%20same%20school%2C%20had%20none.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20every%20Danish%20family%20lives%20in%20perfect%20equality.%20But%20the%20baseline%20feels%20different%20when%20fathers%20are%20treated%20as%20parents%20from%20the%20beginning.%20In%20the%20US%2C%20I%20often%20saw%20motherhood%20framed%20as%20self-erasure.%20The%20mother%20who%20anticipates%20and%20sacrifices%20everything%20is%20often%20treated%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bgood%20parent%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20if%20being%20indispensable%20is%20the%20same%20thing%20as%20being%20loving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20one%20of%20the%20first%20things%20I%20had%20to%20unlearn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229419c79b-f876-4c7a-a50c-321aefb31fc4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20had%20to%20stop%20optimizing%20childhood%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EChildhood%20is%20imagined%20differently%20here%2C%20too.%20I%20grew%20up%20in%20Connecticut%2C%20where%20achievement%20started%20early%20%E2%80%94%20so%20early%20that%20I%20told%20my%20parents%20I%20wanted%20to%20go%20to%20Harvard%20when%20I%20was%206.%20That%20sounds%20absurd%20now%2C%20but%20I'm%20a%20product%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-ivy-league-prep-ultrawealthy-30k-schools-and-resumes-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh-achieving%20environment%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20competition%20could%20begin%20in%20kindergarten.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELiving%20here%2C%20that%20pressure%20seems%20especially%20stark.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-living-in-denmark-shares-differences-in-preschool-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDanish%20early%20childhood%20education%3C%2Fa%3E%20emphasizes%20play%2C%20independence%2C%20outdoor%20time%2C%20and%20social%20development%20over%20grades%2C%20creating%20room%20for%20children%20to%20grow%20before%20measurement%20takes%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20has%20been%20confronting%20for%20me.%20I%20did%20not%20realize%20how%20much%20of%20my%20own%20parenting%20vocabulary%20was%20built%20around%20expressions%20like%20%26quot%3Benrich%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bprepare%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bstimulate%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bschedule.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Denmark%2C%20unstructured%20time%20is%20not%20considered%20wasted%20time%2C%20and%20boredom%20is%20not%20seen%20as%20a%20parental%20failure.%20That%20has%20required%20more%20unlearning%20than%20I%20expected.%20I%20had%20to%20question%20the%20instinct%20that%20told%20me%20a%20good%20mother%20should%20always%20be%20offering%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e2a6aa46-22a9-4963-b016-6dbb0b529145%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20am%20unlearning%20control%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20hardest%20lessons%20to%20overcome%20is%20my%20need%20to%20constantly%20suggest%20the%20activity%2C%20frame%20the%20lesson%2C%20or%20reassure%20myself%20that%20I%20am%20doing%20enough.%20But%20I%20am%20starting%20to%20see%20that%20some%20of%20what%20I%20called%20%26quot%3Battentiveness%26quot%3B%20was%20really%20control%2C%20and%20some%20of%20what%20I%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-surveillance-of-our-kids-making-everyone-more-anxious-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Binvolvement%26quot%3B%20was%20really%20anxiety%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELiving%20in%20Denmark%20has%20shown%20me%20that%20sometimes%20love%20looks%20less%20like%20hovering%20and%20more%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-mom-lived-in-denmark-compares-american-and-nordic-parenting-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrusting%20your%20child%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20explore%2C%20be%20bored%2C%20and%20take%20small%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20do%20not%20think%20Danish%20parents%20love%20their%20children%20more%2C%20or%20that%20Denmark%20has%20solved%20modern%20family%20life.%20I%20also%20do%20not%20think%20American%20parents%20are%20wrong%20to%20be%20more%20anxious.%20In%20the%20US%2C%20there%20are%20legitimate%20reasons%20parents%20feel%20they%20have%20to%20optimize%20everything%3A%20less%20structural%20support%2C%20less%20affordable%20childcare%2C%20and%20more%20competition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20raising%20Aksel%20here%20has%20forced%20me%20to%20see%20how%20much%20of%20what%20I%20once%20considered%20%26quot%3Bgood%20parenting%26quot%3B%20was%20conditioned%20by%20an%20American%20fear%20of%20falling%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20instinct%20is%20still%20in%20me%2C%20and%20maybe%20it%20always%20will%20be.%20But%20I%20notice%20it%20more%20quickly%20now%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20let%20it%20become%20consuming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20maybe%20that%20is%20the%20part%20of%20%26quot%3Bgood%20parenting%26quot%3B%20I%20most%20needed%20to%20unlearn%3A%20the%20idea%20that%20love%20has%20to%20look%20like%20constant%20effort%20to%20count.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdenmark-parenting-culture-american-motherhood-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780575721000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a0c80cdf246b392afc7b6f8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdenmark-parenting-culture-american-motherhood-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Living%20in%20Denmark%20ch