om%2Fphoto%2F131504884.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20thought%20we'd%20avoided%20the%20'terrible%20twos%2C'%20but%20I%20was%20wrong.%20A%20weekly%20fun-day%20helps.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Composite%20image%2C%20on%20the%20left%20the%20author's%20son%20is%20petting%20a%20cow%2C%20and%20on%20the%20right%20the%20author's%20son%20is%20looking%20at%20a%20stingray%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a2072d3b4fb977f35984204%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20takes%20her%20son%20on%20weekly%20outings.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Autumn%20Gavora%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EI'd%20always%20heard%20about%20the%20%26quot%3Bterrible%20twos%26quot%3B%20and%20thought%20we'd%20avoided%20it%20with%20our%20son.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThen%2C%20I%20went%20back%20to%20work%2C%20and%20his%20behavior%20started%20to%20change.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI%20quit%20my%20job%20to%20spend%20more%20time%20with%20him%2C%20but%20he%20still%20wasn't%20happy.%20A%20weekly%20%26quot%3Bfun-day%26quot%3B%20helped.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20having%20my%20son%2C%20I%20heard%20the%20horror%20stories%20of%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftoddler-threw-epic-tantrum-in-public-parenting-lesson-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eterrible%20twos%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20I'd%20stare%20down%20at%20my%20newborn%20and%20think%20there%20was%20absolutely%20no%20way%20this%20little%20bundle%20of%20rolls%20could%20one%20day%20be%20anything%20like%20my%20friends%20were%20describing.%20I%20kept%20that%20mindset%20as%20we%20rolled%20straight%20through%20his%20second%20birthday%2C%20and%20his%20behavior%20remained%20unchanged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20thought%20I%20won%20the%20golden%20ticket.%20My%20toddler%20was%20fantastic%3B%20no%20meltdowns%20in%20sight.%20Like%20any%20naive%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folder-mom-kids-miss-out-physical-activities-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efirst-time%20parent%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20was%20so%20wrong.%20My%20son%20turns%203%20in%20August%2C%20and%20he%20started%20having%20tantrums%20recently.%20However%2C%20after%20asking%20him%20what%20was%20going%20on%2C%20I%20figured%20out%20a%20reason%20for%20the%20behavior%20%E2%80%94%20and%20something%20that%20helped.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2264fac86b-b36a-4754-a7ee-c370c8fbd444%5C%22%3EMy%20son%20had%20a%20hard%20time%20when%20I%20went%20back%20to%20work%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20had%20the%20incredible%20pleasure%20of%20being%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-i-homeschool-kids-while-running-two-businesses-full-time-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehome%20with%20my%20son%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20majority%20of%20his%20life.%20Then%2C%20when%20I%20returned%20to%20the%20office%20full-time%20last%20October%2C%20I%20slowly%20began%20to%20notice%20changes.%20His%20grandpa%20watched%20him%20while%20I%20was%20at%20work%2C%20and%20we%20started%20to%20notice%20he%20wasn't%20listening%20to%20either%20of%20us%20as%20well%3B%20his%20moods%20also%20had%20taken%20a%20dip.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EComing%20home%20every%20day%20and%20seeing%20him%20upset%20broke%20me%20as%20a%20mom.%20In%20January%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-six-figure-job-burnout-working-freelance-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equit%20my%20job%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20return%20home%20full%20time%20to%20be%20with%20him.%20Since%20I've%20returned%20home%2C%20I've%20noticed%20that%20even%20though%20I'm%20here%20and%20we're%20spending%20a%20lot%20more%20time%20together%20again%2C%20his%20moods%20sour.%20He'd%20refuse%20to%20stop%20throwing%20toys%20and%20would%20have%20tantrums%20when%20he%20wouldn't%20listen%20to%20anything%20I%20asked%20him%20to%20do.%20But%20the%20usual%20things%20we'd%20do%20to%20quell%20this%20behavior%20%E2%80%94%20like%20time-outs%20and%20incentives%20for%20good%20behavior%20%E2%80%94%20also%20weren't%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lightbulb%20moment%20went%20off%20when%20I%20sat%20down%20and%20asked%20him%20what%20was%20wrong.%20His%20answer%20was%20%26quot%3BI%20miss%20you%26quot%3B%20or%2C%20worse%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%20see%20you.%26quot%3B%20I%20didn't%20understand%20why%20he%20was%20saying%20this%20when%20I%20was%20literally%20right%20there.%20The%20same%20behaviors%20kept%20happening%2C%20and%20he%20kept%20giving%20the%20same%20answers%3B%20when%20I%20truly%20thought%20about%20it%2C%20I%20realized%20that%20even%20though%20I%20was%20physically%20right%20there%2C%20I%20mentally%20wasn't.%20My%20son%20was%20next%20to%20me%2C%20but%20I%20was%20focusing%20on%20cleaning%2C%20reading%2C%20or%20doing%20other%20things%20I%20thought%20were%20important%2C%20when%20he%20was%20the%20most%20important%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author's%20son%20at%20the%20park.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a207394b4fb977f3598420e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author's%20son%20loves%20going%20to%20the%20park.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Autumn%20Gavora%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229b9dc9db-1fca-430d-b655-910528e38b7c%5C%22%3EI%20wanted%20to%20be%20more%20present%20with%20him%2C%20so%20we%20started%20having%20a%20weekly%20'fun-day'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20realization%20led%20to%20a%20non-negotiable%20once-a-week%20%26quot%3Bfun-day.%26quot%3B%20I%20hated%20feeling%20like%20I%20was%20doing%20my%20son%20a%20disservice%20by%20not%20being%20present%2C%20so%20I%20wanted%20to%20fix%20it.%20I%20created%20an%20activity%20jar%2C%20filled%20with%20folded-up%20pieces%20of%20paper%20with%20special%20places%20on%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20son%20gets%20to%20pick%20from%20the%20jar%2C%20and%20one%20day%20a%20week%2C%20we%20do%20a%20fun%20activity%20together%20that%20gets%20us%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhard-to-limit-my-kids-screen-time-parent-on-phone-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoff%20our%20screens%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20focusing%20on%20each%20other.%20The%20change%20in%20my%20son%20was%20almost%20immediate.%20The%20joyful%20little%20boy%20was%20back.%20There%20were%20fewer%20tantrums%2C%20he%20was%20listening%20again%2C%20and%20he%20was%20visibly%20happy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20few%20months%2C%20we%20have%20spent%20days%20at%20the%20Georgia%20Aquarium%20learning%20about%20his%20favorite%20species%2C%20like%20sting%20rays%2C%20sharks%2C%20and%20the%20brilliant%20red-and-orange%20octopus%20that%20reminds%20him%20of%20The%20Octonauts.%20We%20rode%20on%20a%20trolley%20at%20the%20Atlanta%20Zoo%20and%20learned%20about%20big%20silverback%20gorillas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20favorite%20thing%20to%20do%20is%20pack%20a%20lunch%2C%20have%20a%20picnic%20at%20a%20park%2C%20and%20then%20explore%20by%20hunting%20for%20unique%20rocks%2C%20learning%20about%20the%20different%20trees%2C%20and%20seeing%20how%20many%20different%20animals%20we%20can%20find.%20We've%20also%20been%20painters%20at%20an%20art%20studio%2C%20engineers%20like%20his%20dad%20at%20the%20Atlanta%20Children's%20Museum%2C%20and%20we%20got%20to%20be%20firefighters%20for%20a%20day%20at%20the%20firehouse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fd721f5c-473a-4cc7-be97-fe818e29e77e%5C%22%3EHe%20still%20has%20meltdowns%2C%20but%20things%20have%20improved%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20any%20toddler%2C%20he%20still%20has%20his%20meltdowns.%20I've%20learned%20over%20the%20months%20to%20give%20him%20more%20grace%2C%20as%20simple%20things%20are%20new%20things%20to%20him.%20I've%20realized%20I%20tend%20to%20forget%20that%20he%20is%20experiencing%20everything%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20We%20are%20both%20learning%20and%20growing%20together%20every%20day%2C%20and%20I%20am%20beyond%20happy%20to%20spend%20my%20days%20with%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20time%20together%20has%20shown%20me%20to%20take%20a%20step%20back%20for%20him%20and%20to%20soak%20it%20all%20in.%20Rarely%20do%20I%20hear%20him%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%20see%20you%26quot%3B%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftoddler-tantrums-nothing-worked-book-techniques-helped-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereason%20for%20a%20meltdown%3C%2Fa%3E%20anymore.%20It's%20more%20%26quot%3BI'm%20hungry%26quot%3B%20or%20a%20rebuttal%20against%20me%20telling%20him%20he%20can't%20do%20or%20have%20something%2C%20which%20we%20are%20working%20on.%20With%20summer%20quickly%20approaching%2C%20I%20cannot%20wait%20to%20bring%20him%20to%20more%20places%20to%20explore%20and%20meet%20new%20friends.%20So%20far%2C%20the%20terrible%20twos%20aren't%20as%20terrible%20as%20I%20thought%20they%20would%20be%20once%20we%20figured%20out%20that%20our%20fun-days%20are%20the%20key%20to%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fterrible-twos-toddler-tantrums-weekly-fun-day-helps-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780570261000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a2072d3b4fb977f35984204%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fterrible-twos-toddler-tantrums-weekly-fun-day-helps-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20non-negotiable%20weekly%20'fun-day%26quot%3B%20helps%20with%20my%20toddler's%20tantrums.%20He%20just%20needed%20me%20to%20be%20more%20present.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Autumn%20Gavora)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%2