rth%20Chopra%2C%20entered%20YC's%20fall%202024%20batch%20with%20an%20AI%20shopping%20tool.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAfter%20running%20at%20a%20loss%2C%20they%20pivoted%20through%20five%20to%20six%20ideas%20before%20finding%20success.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20said%20their%20biggest%20mistake%20during%20the%20search%20for%20a%20winning%20app%20was%20how%20they%20handled%20pivots.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Alex%20Ruber%2C%20a%2029-year-old%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%2C%20based%20in%20San%20Francisco.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20five%20months%20after%20being%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-y-combinator-founders-are-pitching-the-ai-boom-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EY%20Combinator%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20my%20cofounder%2C%20Parth%2C%20and%20I%20thought%20we%20might%20have%20to%20give%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20met%20through%20Y%20Combinator's%20Co-founder%20Matching%20Program%2C%20a%20free%20resource%20to%20help%20people%20find%20potential%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-mistakes-founders-make-that-quietly-wreck-cofounder-relationships-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebusiness%20partners%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20January%202024.%20We%20were%20both%20working%20full-time.%20After%20building%20some%20projects%20together%2C%20we%20launched%20an%20AI-powered%20shopping%20tool%20and%20were%20accepted%20into%20Y%20Combinator's%20fall%202024%20batch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20became%20clear%20that%20the%20shopping%20app%20was%20not%20economically%20viable%20and%20was%20running%20at%20a%20loss%2C%20with%20no%20clear%20path%20forward.%20We%20entered%20what%20I%20call%20our%20three-month%20pivot%20hell.%20Within%20those%20three%20months%2C%20we%20tried%20out%20about%20five%20to%20six%20different%20ideas%20and%20almost%20gave%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20we%20built%20a%20very%20simple%20game%20on%20a%20whim%2C%20and%20by%20August%202025%2C%20roughly%20five%20months%20after%20launch%2C%20our%20monthly%20revenue%20had%20reached%20%24144%2C533.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20wants%20to%20talk%20to%20founders%20of%20AI-powered%20companies%20with%20fewer%20than%2010%20workers%2C%20and%20employees%20working%20alongside%20AI%20agents%2C%20to%20understand%20what%20the%20%26quot%3BTiny%20Teams%26quot%3B%20era%20really%20feels%20like%20%E2%80%94%20the%20wins%2C%20the%20fears%2C%20and%20the%20human%20skills%20that%20stand%20out.%20Share%20your%20story%20by%20filling%20out%20this%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLScO-Lptuw9eirYFmkAfOKc1aOvrFIW1jT2FzxuLJSexsTLExg%2Fviewform%3Fusp%3Dheader%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equick%20form%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ec17ceec-b6f7-4b29-8065-c53f1850f2a4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20did%20not%20want%20to%20let%20go%20of%20our%20first%20app%20idea%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EParth%20and%20I%20were%20both%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-coding-agents-tools-software-engineering-jobs-future-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efull-time%20engineers%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20we%20met%20and%20bonded%20over%20our%20love%20of%20building%20projects%20on%20the%20side.%20Also%2C%20we're%20both%20really%20into%20fashion%2C%20especially%20thrifting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20thought%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthrift-shopping-family-budget-furnish-home-buy-luxury-clothes-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esecondhand%20shopping%3C%2Fa%3E%20market%20would%20only%20grow%20as%20concerns%20about%20the%20environment%20grew.%20Combining%20that%20with%20the%20advent%20of%20AI%2C%20we%20built%20a%20basic%20conversational%20search%20engine%20where%20users%20could%20type%20anything%20in%20natural%20language%2C%20like%20%26quot%3BI'm%20looking%20for%20a%20leather%20jacket%20under%20%24500%20with%20two%20stripes%2C%20and%20it%20has%20to%20be%20a%20little%20bit%20worn%20in.%26quot%3B%20The%20engine%20would%20search%20resale%20sites%20like%20Poshmark%2C%20eBay%2C%20Mercari%2C%20and%20ThredUp%2C%20then%20compile%20all%20the%20results%20into%20a%20single%20page.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20loved%20using%20the%20app%20and%20got%20some%20traction%2C%20but%20it%20was%20very%20expensive%20to%20run.%20People%20were%20browsing%20every%20day%2C%20but%20they%20weren't%20necessarily%20buying.%20The%20commission%20we%20made%20on%20the%20final%20sale%20wasn't%20great%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20poured%20so%20much%20time%20and%20energy%20into%20this%2C%20and%20wanted%20to%20continue%20because%20of%20that%2C%20but%20we%20hit%20a%20breaking%20point.%20Eventually%2C%20we%20made%20the%20call%20to%20explore%20other%20ideas%20as%20our%20main%20pursuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f85d36c2-97f4-4bcd-9a47-049d4a8c6ed0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20spent%202%20to%203%20weeks%20on%20each%20new%20idea%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20cycled%20through%20five%20to%20six%20fleshed-out%20ideas%2C%20up%20to%2010%2C%20depending%20on%20how%20you%20define%20an%20idea%20execution.%20We%20tried%20everything%20from%20a%20therapy%20product%20to%20a%20self-journaling%20product%20to%20ideas%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbumble-launching-plans-paid-group-dating-feature-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edating%20apps%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20even%20went%20into%20the%20B2B%20side%20of%20the%20insurance%20and%20paper%20industries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe'd%20constrain%20ourselves%20to%20build%20the%20solution%20in%20one%20to%20two%20days%20so%20that%20we%20could%20put%20it%20in%20front%20of%20real%20users%20through%20friends%2C%20family%2C%20Reddit%2C%20X%2C%20and%20online%20communities%20as%20quickly%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20each%20of%20these%20ideas%2C%20we%20went%20super%20hard%20for%20maybe%20two%20to%20three%20weeks.%20We%20did%20user%20interviews.%20We'd%20also%20determine%20the%20product's%20success%20metrics%2C%20and%20we%20were%20ruthless%20about%20them.%20We%20asked%20ourselves%20a%20simple%20question%3A%20Do%20people%20come%20back%2C%20or%20care%20enough%20to%20pay%3F%20If%20the%20answer%20was%20no%2C%20we'd%20switch%20to%20a%20new%20idea%20very%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConstantly%20trying%20to%20dive%20into%20a%20new%20industry%20or%20space%20put%20a%20huge%20mental%20and%20physical%20strain%20on%20us%2C%20but%20we%20were%20really%20trying%20to%20find%20a%20problem%20we%20could%20help%20solve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227be8d2c7-7ec6-4e72-a3d2-65b2f797845e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ERight%20before%20we%20came%20up%20with%20our%20successful%20app%2C%20we%20hit%20a%20low%20point%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20cycled%20through%20so%20many%20ideas%2C%20and%20the%20metrics%20weren't%20looking%20good.%20We%20were%20completely%20exhausted%20and%20didn't%20know%20what%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20one%20night%20when%20Parth%20and%20I%20decided%20to%20go%20for%20a%20walk.%20We%20both%20wanted%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbala-bangles-founder-burnout-recovery-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etake%20a%20break%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%2C%20honestly%2C%20get%20out%20of%20the%20startup%20world.%20We%20took%20two%20or%20three%20days%20off%20to%20reflect%20on%20what%20went%20right%20and%20what%20went%20wrong%20for%20each%20pursuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20last%20day%2C%20we%20went%20back%20to%20the%20whiteboard.%20We%20decided%20we%20wanted%20to%20build%20in%20the%20consumer%20space.%20That's%20one%20thing%20that%20we%20learned%20from%20that%20whole%20pivot%20hell%3A%20we%20didn't%20love%20B2B.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20started%20making%20observations%20about%20the%20world%20around%20us.%20Being%20a%20founder%20is%20a%20very%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhot-new-breakup-line-startups-founder-mode-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elonely%20experience%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20we%20noticed%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20our%20friends%20and%20family%20were%20worried%20about%20us.%20Every%20time%20they%20checked%20in%20or%20called%2C%20we'd%20always%20be%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20we're%20just%20working.%26quot%3B%20Same%20bland%20answer%20every%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20we%20built%20a%20very%20early%20version%20of%20Candle%2C%20our%20social%20connection%20app%2C%20mainly%20to%20feel%20closer%20to%20our%20loved%20ones%20again.%20It%20gives%20a%20one-question-a-day%20prompt%20for%20both%20people%20to%20answer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ca56f5e3-2a8d-42a8-807b-328b8d2d6709%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20didn't%20have%20any%20metric%20goals%20when%20we%20first%20created%20our%20best%20idea%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20so%20strict%20about%20the%20metrics%20during%20our%20constant%20pivot%20cycle%2C%20but%20we%20didn't%20have%20metrics%20for%20Candle%20right%20away%20because%20it%20wasn't%20one%20of%20the%20ideas%20we%20took%20seriously%20enough%20to%20define%20metrics%20for%20before%20we%20built%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20it%20started%20making%20a%20big%20difference%20in%20our%20own%20relationships.%20The%20retention%20seemed%20really%20good%20organically%20among%20our%20family%20and%20friends.%20We%20started%20measuring%20it%2C%20and%20it%20was%20the%20best%20metric-wise%20of%20our%20ideas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20published%20the%20app%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetflix-game-controller-tops-apple-app-store-chatgpt-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20App%20Store%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20March%202025.%20We%20have%20a%20full-time%20team%20of%20four%2C%20and%20in%20our%20first%20year%2C%20we%20made%20over%20%241%20million%20in%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222209%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20video%20call%20with%20four%20smiling%20people%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a2084272ab5f9757add8e61%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221657%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20full-time%20team%20of%20four%20at%20Candle.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Alex%20Ruber%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2236f5b7a7-e159-4c76-97a4-55ea4f207a0e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20don't%20throw%20AI%20at%20every%20step%2C%20but%20it%20does%20help%20us%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20a%20large%20question%20library%2C%20and%20we're%20actually%20opposed%20to%20AI-generated%20questions%20for%20our%20app.%20We%20feel%20like%20they%20come%20across%20as%20inauthentic%2C%20and%20this%20is%20an%20app%20for%20human%20connection%2C%20so%20we%20have%20human%20question%20writers.%20However%2C%20we%20do%20use%20AI%20to%20edit%20grammar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20use%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-ai-startup-founder-switched-chatgpt-to-claude-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EClaude%20Code%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Codex%20for%20much%20of%20our%20code%20generation%20and%20for%20building%20mini-games%20in%20the%20app.%20We%20don't%20have%20a%20translator%2C%20so%20we've%20started%20using%20AI%20to%20translate%20into%20German%2C%20French%2C%20and%20Spanish.%20This%20has%20worked%20very%20well%2C%20especially%20using%20Gemini%20and%20Claude.%20We%20also%20have%20AI%20recommendations%20for%20activities%20that%20two%20users%20could%20do%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20AI%20to%20recommend%20content%20or%20information%20that%20helps%20two%20people%20connect%20is%20how%20I%20think%20AI%20should%20be%20used%2C%20not%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdating-ai-companion-replika-vs-human-pros-cons-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereplace%20the%20connections%20humans%20form%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221cb538f7-39ec-4aba-83a4-4c5185257853%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20pinpointed%20our%20biggest%20mistake%20and%20learned%20from%20it%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20feel%20so%20passionate%20about%20our%20app.%20Looking%20back%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceos-shared-biggest-career-mistakes-lessons-learned-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20biggest%20mistake%3C%2Fa%3E%20we%20made%20was%20making%20an%20industry%20pivot%20that%20was%20too%20large%20each%20time%20we%20explored%20a%20new%20product%20idea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20picking%20a%20problem%20space%20we%20really%20love%2C%20trying%20our%20solution%2C%20and%2C%20if%20it%20didn't%20work%2C%20switching%20to%20a%20different%20solution%2C%20we%20kept%20switching%20industries.%20We%20lost%20our%20passion%20for%20what%20we%20were%20building%20as%20we%20did%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20advice%20would%20be%20to%20pick%20the%20problem%20space%20and%20not%20change%20it%20very%20easily.%20How%20you%20approach%20that%20problem%20is%20what%20you%20should%20be%20changing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20similar%20story%20to%20share%3F%20If%20so%2C%20please%20reach%20out%20to%20the%20reporter%20at%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aaapplegate%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eaapplegate%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fy-combinator-startup-founder-million-dollar-idea-biggest-mistake-pivots-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780565311000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a21364e2ab5f9757add8fd6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fy-combinator-startup-founder-million-dollar-idea-biggest-mistake-pivots-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20startup%20cofounder%20explains%20