%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780564021000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a20bb86b4fb977f359843c1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-shares-accepted-luxury-brooklyn-home-price-photos-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Brooklyn%20home%20seller%20is%20seeking%20Anthropic%20shares%20or%20bitcoin%20for%20a%20%245.99M%20property%2C%20reflecting%20AI%20equity's%20rise%20in%20real%20estate%20transactions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ktl%40businessinsider.com%20(Katherine%20Tangalakis-Lippert)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20got%20laid%20off%20from%20IBM%20over%202%20years%20ago%20and%20I'm%20still%20unemployed.%20I%20don't%20want%20my%20kids%20to%20feel%20like%20anything%20is%20wrong.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221300%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Fatema%20Ali%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a2044a42e5a80cfe0502c23%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221698%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFatema%20Ali%20was%20laid%20off%20from%20IBM%20in%20April%202024%20and%20is%20still%20looking%20for%20full-time%20work%20more%20than%20two%20years%20later.%3Cp%3EFatema%20Ali%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFatema%20Ali%20was%20laid%20off%20from%20IBM%20in%20April%202024%20and%20is%20still%20searching%20for%20full-time%20work.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20says%20today's%20job%20market%20feels%20harder%20than%20it%20did%20when%20she%20graduated%20during%20the%20Great%20Recession.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELiving%20off%20savings%20has%20helped%20her%20family%20navigate%20financial%20uncertainty%20after%20her%20layoff.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Fatema%20Ali%2C%20a%20job%20seeker%20in%20her%2030s%20who%20lives%20in%20Texas.%20She%20previously%20worked%20for%20IBM%20as%20a%20project%20manager%20before%20being%20laid%20off%20in%202024.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20early%202024%2C%20I%20began%20to%20worry%20that%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-ibm-intern-neurofibromatosis-building-career-high-school-college-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etime%20at%20IBM%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20be%20coming%20to%20an%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20a%20delivery%20project%20manager%20based%20in%20the%20Dallas%20area%20and%20had%20been%20working%20remotely%20since%20joining%20IBM%20in%202018.%20That%20January%2C%20IBM%20announced%20that%20all%20US%20managers%20would%20be%20required%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fibm-wants-managers-return-office-or-get-new-job-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%20to%20an%20office%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20client%20location%20at%20least%20three%20days%20a%20week%20or%20risk%20losing%20their%20jobs.%20There%20was%20an%20office%20about%2015%20minutes%20from%20my%20home%2C%20and%20I%20started%20going%20in%20regularly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%2C%20my%20manager%20started%20warning%20me%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecent-company-layoffs-laying-off-workers-2025%23ibm-said-it-will-cut-thousands-of-jobs-in-the-fourth-quarter-33%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebroader%20layoffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20be%20on%20the%20horizon.%20By%20the%20time%20I%20was%20laid%20off%20in%20April%2C%20I%20wasn't%20completely%20surprised.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20two%20years%20later%2C%20I'm%20still%20looking%20for%20full-time%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223ec008e7-d09d-4d16-ac57-265c447d5e48%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20were%20suddenly%20both%20out%20of%20work%20at%20the%20same%20time%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20made%20the%20layoff%20more%20difficult%20was%20that%20a%20few%20months%20earlier%2C%20my%20husband%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fultimate-guide-quitting-your-job-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eleft%20his%20job%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20pursue%20a%20startup%20idea%20that%20wasn't%20yet%20generating%20income.%20We%20had%20three%20children%20to%20support%2C%20and%20suddenly%20neither%20of%20us%20had%20a%20traditional%20full-time%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20working%20in%20our%20favor%20was%20that%20we%20had%20already%20paid%20off%20our%20house.%20That%20gave%20us%20some%20breathing%20room%20and%20relieved%20some%20financial%20pressure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20so%2C%20there%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20financial%20uncertainty.%20We%20cut%20back%20where%20we%20could%20and%20tried%20to%20live%20more%20simply%2C%20including%20traveling%20less%20with%20the%20kids.%20For%20a%20period%2C%20we%20were%20largely%20living%20off%20savings%20and%20the%20severance%20I%20received%2C%20which%20amounted%20to%20about%20three%20months%20of%20salary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-hired-job-search-white-collar-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elooking%20for%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20immediately%2C%20both%20inside%20and%20outside%20IBM.%20There%20was%20one%20promising%20internal%20opportunity%20I%20applied%20for%2C%20but%20it%20would've%20required%20me%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-to-raleigh-from-new-york-city-mistakes-regrets-surprises-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emove%20to%20North%20Carolina%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20had%20recently%20bought%20a%20home%20in%20Texas%2C%20had%20family%20nearby%2C%20and%20didn't%20want%20to%20uproot%20my%20three%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20I%20focused%20on%20finding%20opportunities%20closer%20to%20home%2C%20primarily%20in%20project%20and%20program%20management%2C%20while%20also%20applying%20for%20roles%20in%20higher%20education%2C%20nonprofits%2C%20and%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20is%20speaking%20with%20workers%20who've%20found%20themselves%20at%20a%20corporate%20crossroads%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20due%20to%20a%20layoff%2C%20resignation%2C%20job%20search%2C%20or%20shifting%20workplace%20expectations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EShare%20your%20story%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLSechTVqVWQve8iqYssNriCXdtwwdgGRixNNZpmslSKBQqIJ8g%2Fviewform%3Fusp%3Dheader%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efilling%20out%20this%20form%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20contacting%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajzinkula%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejzinkula%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20via%20Signal%20at%20jzinkula.29.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22174a7e20-051c-4fb4-b1c4-c941c16cb921%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20job%20search%20feels%20harder%20than%20it%20did%20during%20the%20Great%20Recession%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20graduated%20from%20college%20in%202008%20during%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-warned-great-recession-2008-brooksley-born-wall-street-sexism-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20Great%20Recession%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20job%20market%20was%20difficult.%20Looking%20back%2C%20it%20almost%20feels%20like%20a%20walk%20in%20the%20park%20compared%20with%20what%20I've%20experienced%20over%20the%20last%20two%20years.%20Back%20then%2C%20I%20was%20getting%20more%20interview%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20frustrating%20parts%20of%20the%20process%20has%20been%20dealing%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-department-of-labor-investigator-shares-resume-ats-tips-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eapplicant%20tracking%20systems%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20have%20dozens%20of%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20versions%20for%20different%20roles%20because%20I%20know%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20can%20be%20filtered%20out%20if%20they're%20missing%20the%20right%20keywords.%20It%20feels%20like%20strong%20candidates%20can%20be%20overlooked%20before%20anyone%20has%20a%20chance%20to%20review%20their%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20can%20spend%20hours%20tailoring%20an%20application%20and%20never%20speak%20with%20a%20human%20recruiter.%20It's%20become%20a%20nightmare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20try%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetworking-dos-and-donts-tips-advice-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epeople%20in%20my%20network%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20I%20see%20a%20mutual%20connection%20who%20works%20at%20an%20organization%20where%20I'm%20applying%2C%20I'll%20try%20to%20reconnect%20with%20them%20directly.%20Simply%20applying%20online%20without%20a%20referral%20has%20become%20one%20of%20my%20least%20effective%20job-search%20strategies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20landed%20a%20few%20interviews%20over%20the%20last%20two%20years%20and%20have%20made%20it%20through%20multiple%20rounds%20with%20some%20employers.%20In%20many%20cases%2C%20companies%20ultimately%20chose%20an%20internal%20candidate%20or%20someone%20with%20more%20experience%20in%20a%20specific%20area.%20Occasionally%2C%20I%20check%20LinkedIn%20to%20try%20to%20figure%20out%20who%20ended%20up%20getting%20the%20role%20based%20on%20their%20title%20and%20start%20date.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2208f5ba55-5f27-4dc3-aee6-30aedea3336a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI've%20tried%20to%20make%20the%20most%20of%20my%20time%20away%20from%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I've%20been%20looking%20for%20work%20since%20my%20layoff%2C%20I%20haven't%20always%20been%20consistent%20with%20my%20applications.%20I%20spent%20time%20helping%20my%20husband%20with%20his%20startup%20and%20devoted%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20to%20caring%20for%20my%20youngest%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20my%20husband%20decided%20to%20focus%20less%20on%20his%20startup%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiggest-mistakes-women-make-returning-to-work-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ereturn%20to%20the%20workforce%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20landing%20a%20new%20job%20in%20November.%20That%20provided%20some%20financial%20relief%20for%20our%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20my%20children%20have%20gotten%20older%2C%20I've%20also%20had%20more%20freedom%20to%20focus%20on%20my%20career%20again.%20By%20the%20middle%20of%20last%20year%2C%20I%20became%20much%20more%20consistent%20with%20my%20job%20search.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I'm%20still%20looking%20for%20work%2C%20I've%20scaled%20back%20my%20job%20search%20somewhat%20in%20recent%20months%20to%20spend%20more%20time%20pursuing%20projects%20with%20my%20husband%2C%20notably%20P1loop%2C%20an%20app%20we%20launched%20together.%20My%20husband%20used%20his%20experience%20as%20an%20iOS%20developer%20to%20help%20build%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20app%20is%20designed%20to%20help%20teams%20communicate%20about%20urgent%20operational%20issues.%20It%20isn't%20generating%20any%20income%20yet%2C%20but%20we're%20hopeful.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EMy%20layoff%20experience%20has%20forced%20me%20to%20rethink%20stability%2C%20take%20a%20risk%2C%20and%20try%20to%20build%20something%20meaningful%20from%20scratch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222a70b4d8-44e5-4506-a832-872ca0cb6749%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20biggest%20lesson%20I've%20learned%20is%20patience%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20working%20since%20I%20was%2019%2C%20and%20I'm%20looking%20forward%20to%20returning%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20job%20search%20has%20been%20stressful%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20want%20that%20pressure%20to%20show%20on%20my%20face.%20I%20don't%20want%20my%20children%20to%20feel%20like%20there%20is%20anything%20wrong.%20I%20want%20to%20carry%20on%20with%20the%20day%20and%20stay%20grounded%20as%20best%20as%20I%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20unemployed%20hasn't%20felt%20like%20much%20of%20a%20break.%20When%20you're%20dealing%20with%20financial%20uncertainty%2C%20caring%20for%20children%2C%20looking%20for%20work%2C%20and%20trying%20to%20build%20something%20new%2C%20your%20mind%20is%20always%20racing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20best%20advice%20to%20anyone%20going%20through%20this%20is%20to%20stay%20patient%2C%20whether%20you've%20worked%20really%20hard%20and%20things%20are%20going%20exactly%20the%20way%20you%20hoped%2C%20or%20things%20aren't%20falling%20into%20place%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I'm%20still%20looking%20for%20the%20right%20opportunity%2C%20I've%20learned%20the%20importance%20of%20staying%20the%20course.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaid-off-ibm-job-search-tech-manager-unemployed-great-recession-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780563902000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a2044ae2ab5f9757add8762%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaid-off-ibm-job-search-tech-manager-unemployed-great-recession-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Fatema%20Ali%20was%20laid%20off%20from%20IBM%20in%202024.%20Over%20two%20years%20later%2C%20she's%20still%20looking%20for%20work%20and%20says%20the%20job%20search%20feels%20harder%20than%20it%20did%20in%202008.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jzinkula%40insider.com%20(Jacob%20Zinkula)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22They%20booked%20dream%20acting%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20then%20lost%20them%20to%20AI%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226463%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Hannah%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a2033a42e5a80cfe0502b80%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224847%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EAdam%20Amengual%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHannah%20Lowery%20expected%20to%20lose%20acting%20jobs%20to%20rivals%20%E2%80%94%20but%20not%20to%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20the%2019-year-old%20actor%2C%20based%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20was%20thrilled%20to%20find%20out%20she'd%20been%20cast%20in%20a%20new%20show%20about%20the%20cutthroat%20world%20of%20ice%20skating.%20Then%20came%20the%20bad%20news%3A%20The%20project%20was%20shifting%20entirely%20to%20AI.%20She%20and%20the%20other%20humans%20were%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20disheartening%20because%20the%20amount%20of%20jobs%20that%20everyone%20would%20have%20in%20that%20production%2C%20and%20the%20creativity%20that%20everyone%20would%20bring%20to%20that%20story%2C%20is%20now%20just%20completely%20gone%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELowery's%20experience%20shows%20how%20actors'%20AI%20nightmare%20scenario%20is%20becoming%20a%20reality%20in%20one%20corner%20of%20Hollywood%20%E2%80%94%20the%20fast-growing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicro-dramas-reelshort-dramabox-billion-dollar-business-in-us-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%241.3%20billion%20industry%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20%26quot%3Bmicro%20dramas%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20short-form%20series%20designed%20for%20mobile%20viewing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20tabindex%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20data-media-container%3D%5C%22image%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22img%5C%22%20data-e2e-name%3D%5C%22image-figure-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cimg%20data-content-type%3D%5C%22image%2Fjpeg%5C%22%20data-srcs%3D%5C%22%7B%26quot%3Bhttps%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a20354bb4fb977f35983b17%26quot%3B%3A%7B%26quot%3BcontentType%26quot%3B%3A%26quot%3Bimage%2Fjpeg%26quot%3B%2C%26quot%3BaspectRatioW%26quot%3B%3A4160%2C%26quot%3BaspectRatioH%26quot%3B%3A5200%7D%7D%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a20354bb4fb977f35983b17%3Fwidth%3D1300%26format%3Djpeg%26auto%3Dwebp%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Hannah%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%220%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cspan%3E%5Cn%3Cfigcaption%20data-e2e-name%3D%5C%22image-caption%5C%22%3E%5Cn%26quot%3BI%20just%20don't%20think%20AI%20can%20replace%20any%20of%20that%20pure%2C%20beautiful%20emotion%20that%20comes%20from%20the%20human%20body%2C%26quot%3B%20Lowery%20said.%5Cn%3Cspan%20data-e2e-name%3D%5C%22image-source%5C%22%3E%5CnAdam%20Amengual%20for%20BI%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sector%20had%20become%20a%20rare%20bright%20spot%20for%20actors%20slogging%20through%20a%20yearslong%20slump%20in%20film%20and%20TV%20production%2C%20especially%20in%20Los%20Angeles.%20Now%20it's%20turning%20into%20ground%20zero%20for%20AI%20displacement%20of%20human%20actors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBlake%20Manning%2C%20a%2021-year-old%20actor%20who%20grew%20up%20in%20Orange%20County%2C%20was%20tapped%20to%20play%20a%20renegade%20hockey%20star%20in%20April%20before%20finding%20out%20that%20the%20project%20was%20flipping%20to%20AI.%20Faith%20Orta%2C%20an%20actor%20who%20appeared%20in%20half%20a%20dozen%20short%20series%20this%20year%2C%20said%20she%20lost%20a%20role%20to%20AI%20less%20than%20two%20weeks%20before%20filming%20was%20set%20to%20begin.%20Rebecca%20Berg%2C%20another%20short-drama%20star%2C%20said%20her%20audition%20calls%20have%20been%20drying%20up.%20She%20had%20five%20calls%20in%20a%20recent%20week%2C%20down%20from%20the%20usual%2020%20to%2030.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20big%20driver%20of%20the%20shift%20is%20cost%20savings.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkhosla-ventures-jeffrey-katzenberg-backing-trueshort-ai-vertical-film-app-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrueShort%2C%20a%20new%20AI%20film%20startup%3C%2Fa%3E%20backed%20by%20Khosla%20Ventures%20and%20Jeffrey%20Katzenberg's%20WndrCo%2C%20said%20it%20can%20make%2020-%20to%2030-minute%20shows%20for%20%241%2C000%20to%20%243%2C000%20each%20%E2%80%94%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20typical%20%24100%2C000%20to%20%24300%2C000%20cost%20of%20those%20using%20human%20actors.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpitch-deck-storeel-raised-millions-build-ai-micro-dramas-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBeijing-based%20startup%20StoReel%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20it%20can%20make%20an%20hourlong%20series%20using%20AI%20for%20%2420%2C000%20to%20%2440%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20China%2C%20where%20micro%20dramas%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0also%20called%20%26quot%3Bverticals%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20first%20gained%20popularity%2C%20a%20significant%20share%20of%20the%20work%20has%20already%20shifted%20to%20AI.%20These%20AI%20productions%20are%20expected%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ce.cn%2Fxwzx%2Fgnsz%2Fgdxw%2F202603%2Ft20260311_2818424.shtml%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edrive%20around%20%243.5%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20revenue%20this%20year%2C%20according%20to%20state-run%20media.%20It%20pegged%20the%20overall%20Chinese%20micro%20drama%20market%20at%20more%20than%20%2414%20billion%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20tabindex%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20data-media-container%3D%5C%22image%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22img%5C%22%20data-e2e-name%3D%5C%22image-figure-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cimg%20data-content-type%3D%5C%22image%2Fjpeg%5C%22%20data-srcs%3D%5C%22%7B%26quot%3Bhttps%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a2034b9b4fb977f35983b07%26quot%3B%3A%7B%26quot%3BcontentType%26quot%3B%3A%26quot%3Bimage%2Fjpeg%26quot%3B%2C%26quot%3BaspectRatioW%26quot%3B%3A4160%2C%26quot%3BaspectRatioH%26quot%3B%3A5200%7D%7D%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a2034b9b4fb977f35983b07%3Fwidth%3D1300%26format%3Djpeg%26auto%3Dwebp%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Blake%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%220%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cspan%3E%5Cn%3Cfigcaption%20data-e2e-name%3D%5C%22image-caption%5C%22%3E%5CnManning%20said%20he's%20been%20taking%20acting%20classes%20on%20and%20off%20for%20around%20six%20years.%C2%A0%5Cn%3Cspan%20data-e2e-name%3D%5C%22image-source%5C%22%3E%5CnAdam%20Amengual%20for%20BI%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EHollywood's%20broader%20film%20and%20television%20industry%20could%20be%20next.%20Members%20of%20the%20actors'%20union%2C%20SAG-AFTRA%2C%20are%20voting%20on%20a%20contract%20proposal%20that%20introduces%20some%20limitations%20on%20AI%20actors%2C%20but%20still%20allows%20producers%20to%20bargain%20for%20the%20use%20of%20synthetic%20performers%20as%20long%20as%20it%20brings%20%26quot%3Bsignificant%20additional%20value.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20technology%20is%20already%20making%20its%20way%20into%20mainstream%20filmmaking.%20The%20movie%20%26quot%3BAs%20Deep%20as%20the%20Grave%26quot%3B%20grabbed%20headlines%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%20March%20for%20using%20an%20AI%20replica%20of%20the%20late%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fval-kilmer-ai-movie-as-deep-as-the-grave-trailer-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVal%20Kilmer%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BHell%20Grind%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20mostly%20AI-generated%20action%20movie%20from%20startup%20Higgsfield%20AI%2C%20premiered%20in%20May%20at%20March%C3%A9%20du%20Film%20in%20Cannes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BActors%20are%20existentially%20worried%20about%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Zak%20Barnett%2C%20an%20acting%20coach%20who's%20spent%20decades%20training%20Hollywood%20aspirants.%20%26quot%3BIt%20feels%20like%20verticals%20are%20the%20first%20real%20testing%20ground.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22886e0815-c4ee-4c5a-b23e-9bcadee4283c%5C%22%3E'A%20lot%20of%20people%20rely%20on%20this%20for%20work'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMicro%20dramas%2C%20which%20feature%20soap-opera%20plotlines%20like%20%26quot%3BThe%20Fake%20Debutante%20and%20the%20True%20Billionaire%2C%26quot%3B%20experienced%20rapid%20growth%20in%20the%20US%20last%20year.%20Major%20streamers%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpeacock-reelshort-micro-dramas-bravo-hollywood-short-form-vertical-video-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EParamount%2B%20and%20Peacock%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20begun%20exploring%20the%20format.%20Issa%20Rae%2C%20an%20actor%20and%20co-creator%20of%20HBO's%20%26quot%3BInsecure%2C%26quot%3B%20launched%20a%20micro%20drama%20series%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20shows%20have%20become%20an%20important%20source%20of%20jobs%20for%20Los%20Angeles%20actors%20since%20many%20productions%20have%20moved%20out%20of%20Hollywood%20to%20places%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhollywood-leaving-los-angeles-remote-work-tv-movies-money-streaming-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efavorable%20tax%20incentives%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20as%20London%2C%20Vancouver%2C%20and%20states%20like%20Georgia%20and%20New%20Mexico.%20In%20the%20first%20half%20of%20May%2C%20nearly%20a%20third%20(28%25)%20of%20the%20LA%20casting%20opportunities%20listed%20on%20the%20Actors%20Access%20jobs%20portal%20were%20for%20roles%20in%20verticals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELuke%20Dodge%2C%20a%2020-year-old%20actor%20who%20followed%20his%20parents%20into%20entertainment%2C%20said%20he%20earns%20between%20%241%2C200%20and%20%242%2C000%20per%20day%20on%20a%20nine-%20or%2010-day%20micro-drama%20shoot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227135%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Luke%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a2038082ab5f9757add86eb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225352%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDodge%20grew%20up%20in%20Baltimore%20and%20decided%20to%20leave%20college%20to%20pursue%20acting%20full-time.%3Cp%3EAdam%20Amengual%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20just%20keep%20coming%20in%2C%20it's%20almost%20like%20working%20a%209-to-5%2C%20they're%20so%20rhythmic%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20verticals.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20able%20to%20quit%20my%20jobs%2C%20and%20actually%20have%20a%20nice%20little%20jump%20in%20this%20industry%2C%20which%20is%20cool.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20other%20young%20actors%2C%20Dodge%20has%20noticed%20AI%20creeping%20into%20his%20work%20this%20year.%20A%20production%20company%20recently%20sent%20him%20an%20approval%20request%20seeking%20permission%20to%20include%20an%20AI%20version%20of%20him%20in%20additional%20scenes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDodge%20is%20worried%20about%20micro%20dramas%20fully%20pivoting%20to%20AI%20actors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20people%20rely%20on%20this%20for%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20would%20be%2C%20definitely%2C%20very%20destructive%20if%20they%20went%20AI.%20We%20would%20all%20be%20out%20of%20jobs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOrta%2C%20a%2026-year-old%20actor%20who%20regularly%20stars%20in%20short%20dramas%20including%20%26quot%3BMarrying%20a%20Prisoner%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BRooming%20with%20the%20Devil%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20she%20was%20cast%20in%20a%20lead%20role%20in%20February.%20She%20said%20a%20producer%20then%20told%20her%20that%20the%20series%20was%20shifting%20to%20AI%20and%20that%20they%20could%20make%2060%20AI%20shows%20with%20the%20same%20budget.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20the%20decision%20cost%20her%20other%20opportunities%20she'd%20passed%20up%20for%20the%20rare%20chance%20to%20play%20a%20strong%20female%20lead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20get%20to%20do%20such%20roles%20so%20often%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BShe%20was%20super%20strong.%20I%20was%20sad%20it%20was%20taken%20away.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228192%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20stars%20of%20the%20short%20drama%20%26quot%3BWings%20of%20Fire%3A%20The%20Dragon%20Slayer%20Is%20My%20Ex-Lover%26quot%3B%20spoke%20at%20a%20screening%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20County.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a207f9c2ab5f9757add8e22%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20stars%20of%20the%20short%20drama%20%26quot%3BWings%20of%20Fire%3A%20The%20Dragon%20Slayer%20Is%20My%20Ex-Lover%26quot%3B%20spoke%20at%20a%20screening%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20County.%3Cp%3ETiffany%20Rose%2FGetty%20Images%20for%20ReelShort%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sudden%20shift%20has%20sent%20a%20chill%20through%20the%20vertical%20community.%20Short%20dramas%20have%20provided%20a%20steady%20source%20of%20income%20and%20offered%20an%20on-ramp%20for%20unproven%20actors%20who%20otherwise%20would%20have%20had%20to%20settle%20for%20background%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20100%25%20my%20income%2C%26quot%3B%20Berg%20said.%20%26quot%3BMy%20hope%20is%20to%20make%20TV%20shows%20and%20movies%2C%20but%20I'm%20not%20an%20established%20TV%20and%20film%20actor%20yet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225031b620-cad0-4902-a793-c702a1bc5977%5C%22%3EReviews%20are%20%E2%80%A6%20mixed%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGuy%20Chachkes%2C%20a%20film%20producer%2C%20said%20he's%20watched%20around%2015%20verticals%20featuring%20AI%20characters%2C%20and%20their%20performances%20felt%20fake.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20problem%20is%20they're%20not%20emotionally%20believable%2C%20and%20as%20humans%20we're%20really%20good%20at%20calling%20out%20really%20minute%20details%20that%20feel%20fake%20to%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20Chachkes%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhether%20that's%20important%20or%20not%2C%20that%20is%20what%20time%20will%20tell.%20The%20acting%20is%20definitely%20not%20there%20to%20mimic%20real%2C%20true%20human%20emotion.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%