igure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EWalmart's%20Code%20Puppy%20aims%20to%20avoid%20vendor%20lock-in%2C%20offering%20flexibility%20with%20diverse%20AI%20models.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMike%20Pfaffenberger%20developed%20Code%20Puppy%20to%20prevent%20AI%20dependency%20and%20reduce%20tech%20costs%20for%20Walmart.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECode%20Puppy%20has%20gone%20viral%20inside%20Walmart%20and%20is%20used%20by%20VPs%20as%20well%20as%20store%20managers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI%20recently%20asked%20a%20startup%20CEO%20for%20his%20take%20on%20the%20best%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-coding-boom-more-software-shipped-no-hit-quality-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20coding%20tools%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20mentioned%20the%20usual%20suspects%3A%20OpenAI's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-ceo-codex-dan-shipper-every-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECodex%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Anthropic's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-ai-breakthrough-vibe-coding-revolution-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EClaude%20Code%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20he%20brought%20up%20a%20less%20familiar%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20another%20coding%20agent%2C%20Code%20Puppy%2C%20built%20by%20an%20amazing%20guy%20called%20Mike%20Pfaffenberger%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fiamazon-fix-groceries-beat-walmart-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EWalmart%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3B%20this%20CEO%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20got%20masses%20of%20usage%20in%20Walmart.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tip%20sent%20me%20down%20a%20rabbit%20hole%20that%20revealed%20something%20much%20bigger%20than%20another%20AI%20coding%20assistant.%20Code%20Puppy%20is%20part%20of%20Walmart's%20effort%20to%20avoid%20what%20many%20technology%20executives%20fear%20could%20become%20one%20of%20the%20defining%20business%20problems%20of%20the%20AI%20era%3A%20getting%20locked%20into%20a%20handful%20of%20powerful%20providers.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20risk%20is%20familiar.%20Companies%20rush%20to%20adopt%20a%20breakthrough%20technology%2C%20redesign%20their%20systems%20around%20it%2C%20and%20then%20discover%20they've%20become%20dependent%20on%20a%20small%20number%20of%20suppliers.%20Switching%20becomes%20too%20expensive%2C%20disruptive%2C%20or%20risky.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20happened%20with%20IBM.%20It%20happened%20again%20with%20cloud%20computing.%20Now%2C%20many%20companies%20worry%20that%20it%20could%20happen%20with%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECode%20Puppy%20is%20Walmart's%20attempt%20to%20avoid%20that%20fate.%20It's%20become%20even%20more%20important%20lately%2C%20as%20companies%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftokenmaxxing-debate-uber-exec-viral-ai-costs-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eblow%20through%20tech%20budgets%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20spending%20millions%20of%20dollars%20on%20AI%20coding%20tools%20and%20agents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e06f251e-193c-4a83-8d66-b7034312c98b%5C%22%3EPfaffenberger's%20flex%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECode%20Puppy%20was%20created%20by%20Pfaffenberger%2C%20a%20distinguished%20engineer%20in%20Walmart's%20Global%20Tech%20group.%20The%20AI%20coding%20assistant%20helps%20developers%20write%2C%20edit%2C%20test%2C%20and%20manage%20software%20using%20natural-language%20instructions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20Claude%20Code%20and%20Codex%2C%20it%20can%20build%20features%2C%20fix%20bugs%2C%20and%20analyze%20projects.%20But%20unlike%20many%20rivals%2C%20Code%20Puppy%20isn't%20tied%20to%20a%20single%20AI%20model%20or%20provider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20it%20can%20work%20with%20dozens%20of%20models%20from%20different%20suppliers%2C%20allowing%20developers%20to%20switch%20between%20them%2C%20compare%20results%2C%20or%20use%20several%20at%20once.%20It%20can%20also%20distribute%20workloads%20across%20providers%2C%20helping%20avoid%20usage%20limits%20and%20control%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20flexibility%20is%20central%20to%20Pfaffenberger's%20vision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20gives%20us%20the%20ability%20to%20not%20be%20locked%20into%20a%20vendor%20and%20have%20freedom%20to%20control%20and%20integrate%20with%20our%20own%20internal%20systems%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20during%20a%20presentation%20posted%20on%20YouTube%20in%20late%20April.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222ff2fb8e-1fd6-4696-9202-1269ccbd5f92%5C%22%3ECost%20control%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20approach%20has%20multiple%20benefits.%20First%20up%3A%20Code%20Puppy%20could%20potentially%20save%20Walmart%20money%20on%20tokens%2C%20the%20main%20unit%20of%20AI%20usage.%20If%20one%20AI%20model%20provider%20increases%20token%20prices%20or%20introduces%20stricter%20rate%20limits%2C%20the%20system%20can%20help%20developers%20switch%20to%20cheaper%20models%20relatively%20easily.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECode%20Puppy%20works%20with%20models%20from%20OpenAI%2C%20Google%2C%20Anthropic%2C%20and%20dozens%20of%20other%20providers%2C%20according%20to%20the%20project's%20public%20Github%20page.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20instead%20of%20sending%20every%20request%20to%20the%20same%20AI%20model%2C%20Code%20Puppy%20can%20be%20set%20up%20to%20automatically%20rotate%20between%20multiple%20models.%20That%20spreads%20workloads%2C%20reducing%20the%20risk%20of%20hitting%20rate%20limits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227b06b6bd-c47c-41f2-a019-ad4c2e7b1f1a%5C%22%3ECode%20control%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECode%20Puppy%20is%20also%20about%20control%2C%20particularly%20over%20codebases%2C%20the%20vast%20collections%20of%20software%20code%20that%20underpin%20most%20modern%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20coding%20tools%20like%20Claude%20Code%20and%20Codex%20are%20helping%20companies%20generate%20software%20at%20unprecedented%20speed%2C%20causing%20codebases%20to%20grow%20beyond%20what%20human%20developers%20can%20realistically%20maintain%20on%20their%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20creates%20a%20potential%20dependency%3A%20if%20a%20codebase%20was%20largely%20built%20with%20Claude%20Code%20or%20Codex%2C%20companies%20may%20find%20they%20need%20to%20keep%20paying%20for%20those%20same%20tools%20to%20maintain%2C%20update%2C%20and%20understand%20the%20software%20they've%20created.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20Pfaffenberger%20said%20Code%20Puppy%20was%20a%20little%20more%20expensive%20than%20just%20using%20AI%20coding%20services%20such%20as%20Cursor%20or%20Windsurf.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20what%20I%20really%2C%20really%20liked%20about%20it%20was%20I%20was%20in%20control%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20during%20his%20recent%20presentation.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20willing%20to%20pay%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20money%20to%20have%20my%20own%20source%20code%20base%20that%20nobody%20can%20mess%20with.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ff6720c7-b8dc-4765-8980-144df6eec6da%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BEnshittification%26quot%3B%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20moment%2C%20Anthropic%20and%20OpenAI%20are%20competing%20intensely%20with%20Cursor%2C%20Google%2C%20and%20others%20for%20AI%20coding%20market%20share.%20That%20means%20these%20services%20are%20still%20relatively%20affordable%20and%20flexible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Pfaffenberger%20warned%20this%20could%20change%2C%20given%20how%20previous%20technology%20waves%20evolved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20presentation%2C%20he%20described%20this%20cycle%20of%20adoption%20and%20lock-in%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Benshittification%26quot%3B%20of%20tech.%20He%20showed%20a%20slide%20describing%20the%20process%20and%20how%20AI%20is%20intensifying%20it%20this%20time%20round.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20found%20the%20slide%20on%20CodePuppy's%20public%20GitHub%20page.%20Because%20the%20presentation%20was%20stored%20as%20code%20instead%20of%20a%20PowerPoint%20deck%2C%20BI%20used%20ChatGPT%20to%20generate%20a%20viewable%20image%20of%20the%20slide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221486%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20slide%20from%20a%20presentation%20by%20Walmart%20Distinguished%20Engineer%20Mike%20Pfaffenberger%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a1f6c352e5a80cfe05029bd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22844%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20slide%20from%20a%20presentation%20by%20Walmart%20Distinguished%20Engineer%20Mike%20Pfaffenberger%3Cp%3ECode%20Puppy%20public%20Github%20page%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEnshittification%2C%20coined%20by%20writer%20Cory%20Doctorow%2C%20describes%20how%20technology%20platforms%20often%20become%20less%20attractive%20to%20users%20over%20time%20as%20companies%20seek%20to%20increase%20profits%20and%20exert%20more%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20really%2C%20I'm%20kind%20of%20proud%20of%20what%20I%20built%20here%20and%20just%20proud%20to%20be%20separated%20from%20what%20I%20would%20say%20is%20the%20investor-funded%20slop%20cycle%2C%26quot%3B%20Pfaffenberger%20said%20in%20his%20presentation.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20kind%20of%20like%20the%20gist%20of%20this%20slide.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a33fe8a8-139b-473a-9f6a-764058702594%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BHelpless%26quot%3B%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPfaffenberger's%20concerns%20stem%20partly%20from%20his%20own%20experience%20as%20an%20enthusiastic%20user%20of%20AI%20coding%20tools.%20He%20said%20he%20began%20building%20Code%20Puppy%20after%20watching%20turbulence%20in%20the%20market%20for%20AI%20coding%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20when%20Windsurf%20appeared%20close%20to%20being%20acquired%20by%20OpenAI%2C%20Anthropic%20pulled%20access%20to%20one%20of%20its%20most%20popular%20models%20from%20the%20platform.%20Around%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Cursor%20sharply%20reduced%20usage%20limits%2C%20making%20heavy%20use%20of%20its%20service%20substantially%20more%20expensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20looking%20at%20all%20this%20happen%20and%20I%20felt%20kind%20of%20helpless%2C%26quot%3B%20Pfaffenberger%20said%20during%20the%20presentation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20he%20built%20his%20own%20alternative.%20The%20first%20version%20took%20only%20a%20few%20hours%20to%20create.%20Pfaffenberger%20then%20used%20the%20software%20to%20improve%20itself%2C%20allowing%20the%20coding%20assistant%20to%20help%20develop%20new%20versions%20of%20Code%20Puppy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22aedb8aeb-8ebc-4ae2-957b-54c09e895821%5C%22%3EGoing%20viral%20inside%20Walmart%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20project%20struck%20a%20chord%20inside%20Walmart.%20The%20Code%20Puppy%20team%20was%20given%20an%20award%20during%20a%20Walmart%20tech%20all-hands%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20a%20LinkedIn%20post%2C%20Walmart%20SVP%20Dave%20Glick%20said%20Code%20Puppy%20had%20spread%20well%20beyond%20engineering%20teams%2C%20with%20everyone%20from%20tech%20VPs%20to%20store%20managers%20using%20it%20to%20create%20simple%20automations%20and%20bring%20new%20ideas%20to%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPfaffenberger%20said%20Code%20Puppy%20%26quot%3Bkind%20of%20went%20viral%20inside%20of%20Walmart.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EQian%20Li%2C%20cofounder%20of%20startup%20DBOS%2C%20highlighted%20Pfaffenberger's%20advocacy%20for%20using%20an%20%26quot%3BLLM%20council.%26quot%3B%20The%20idea%20is%20simple%3A%20instead%20of%20trusting%20one%20AI%20system%2C%20ask%20several%20models%20to%20tackle%20the%20same%20problem%20and%20compare%20their%20answers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20approach%20reflects%20a%20broader%20philosophy%20behind%20the%20project.%20Rather%20than%20relying%20on%20one%20AI%20provider%2C%20Walmart%20can%20maintain%20flexibility%20to%20switch%20models%20as%20prices%2C%20performance%2C%20and%20capabilities%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22311f05a0-28e5-406f-9d21-f14fa38be88b%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BNightmare%20scenario%26quot%3B%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPfaffenberger%20is%20unusually%20outspoken%20about%20why%20that%20matters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20same%20presentation%2C%20he%20argued%20that%20the%20AI%20industry%20has%20become%20a%20circular%20ecosystem.%20AI%20model%20companies%20raise%20money%20to%20buy%20computing%20power%20from%20Nvidia.%20AI%20application%20startups%20raise%20money%20to%20buy%20access%20to%20those%20models.%20Users%20receive%20heavily%20subsidized%20services%20whose%20economics%20may%20not%20yet%20be%20sustainable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20Pfaffenberger%20warned%2C%20somebody%20has%20to%20pay%20the%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20just%20see%20this%2C%20like%2C%20nightmare%20scenario%20where%E2%80%A6%20we%20as%20users%20who%20are%20not%20part%20of%20this%20agentic%20AI%20bubble%2C%20we%20need%20to%20do%20everything%20we%20can%20to%20protect%20ourselves%20from%20when%20that%20bubble%20goes%20pop%20and%20there's%20no%20access%20to%20tokens%20or%20software%20or%20whatever%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20the%20presentation.%20%26quot%3BThat%20was%20what%20motivated%20me%20to%20write%20Code%20Puppy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOh%2C%20I%20forgot%2C%20I%20forgot%20this%20part%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BWalmart%20does%20require%20me%20to%20say%20that%2C%20like%2C%20all%20of%20my%20opinions%20are%20my%20own.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20build%20our%20tools%20to%20be%20platform%20agnostic%2C%20which%20gives%20us%20the%20flexibility%20to%20work%20with%20the%20best%20partners%20and%20capabilities%20across%20the%20industry.%20Our%20strategy%20is%20not%20to%20lock%20ourselves%20into%20one%20vendor%20or%20model%2C%20but%20to%20give%20associates%20access%20to%20the%20right%20tools%20for%20the%20right%20work%20as%20the%20technology%20continues%20to%20evolve%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Walmart%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3ESign%20up%20for%20BI's%20Tech%20Memo%20newsletter%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsubscription%2Fnewsletter%2Ftech-memo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E.%20Reach%20out%20to%20me%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aabarr%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabarr%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-code-puppy-ai-anthropic-claude-code-openai-codex-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780563603000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a1f5e622ab5f9757add84b1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-code-puppy-ai-anthropic-claude-code-openai-codex-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Walmart's%20viral%20Code%20Puppy%20AI%20tool%20helps%20avoid%20vendor%20lock-in%2C%20cut%20costs%2C%20and%20reduce%20dependence%20on%20Claude%20Code%20and%20Codex.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22abarr%40businessinsider.com%20(Alistair%20Barr)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22This%20startup%20will%20clean%20your%20apartment%20for%20free%2C%20if%20AI%20can%20watch%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222037%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Shift%20cleaner%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a1f56f6b4fb977f359838dd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221528%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EShift%20is%20part%20of%20microagi%2C%20a%20German%20AI%20research%20lab.%3Cp%3EShift%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EShift%20cleaners%20wear%20head-mounted%20cameras%20while%20doing%20household%20chores.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20footage%20is%20turned%20into%20training%20data%20for%20AI%20labs%20and%20robotics%20companies.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShift%20is%20part%20of%20microagi%2C%20a%20German%20lab%20founded%20by%20Formula%20One%20engineers%20and%20an%20AI%20researcher.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20New%20York%20City%2C%20where%20almost%20nothing%20is%20free%2C%20a%20startup%20called%20Shift%20Robotics%20is%20offering%20to%20clean%20your%20apartment%20for%20%240.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20a%20catch%3A%20The%20cleaners%20wear%20head-mounted%20cameras%20that%20record%20first-person%20footage%20as%20they%20do%20dishes%2C%20mop%20floors%2C%20and%20fold%20laundry.%20That%20footage%20is%20turned%20into%20training%20data%20for%20AI%20labs%20and%20robotics%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFew%20people%20had%20heard%20of%20Shift%20before%20last%20week.%20Then%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FjoinshiftX%2Fstatus%2F2060044783519735987%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaunch%20video%3C%2Fa%3E%20went%20viral%2C%20drawing%20more%20than%208%20million%20views.%20The%20initial%20250%20cleaning%20sessions%20sold%20out%20almost%20immediately.%20%26quot%3BWe%20had%20thousands%20and%20thousands%20of%20people%20trying%20to%20book%2C%26quot%3B%20Harry%20Kilberg%2C%20Shift's%20US%20General%20Manager%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShift%20is%20part%20of%20a%20growing%20scramble%20for%20real-world%20data%20as%20AI%20companies%20move%20from%20chatbots%20to%20machines%20that%20can%20work%20in%20homes%2C%20warehouses%2C%20and%20factories.%20Sam%20Altman%20has%20declared%20robotics%20OpenAI's%20next%20frontier%2C%20while%20Nvidia%2C%20Meta%2C%20and%20Tesla%20are%20all%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsilicon-valleys-new-slogan-lets-get-physical-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eramping%20up%3C%2Fa%3E%20their%20own%20robotics%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKilberg%2C%20who%20stars%20in%20the%20launch%20video%2C%20said%20he%20expected%20the%20frenzied%20response.%20%26quot%3BWe%20knew%20this%20idea%20is%20world-changing%2C%20so%20we%20thought%20it%20would%20go%20viral%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShift%20is%20the%20consumer-facing%20brand%20of%20microagi%2C%20a%20research%20lab%20founded%20in%20a%20Munich%20hacker%20house%20last%20year.%20The%20lab%2C%20headquartered%20in%20Germany%2C%20says%20it%20is%20working%20on%20%26quot%3Bend-to-end%20physical%20AGI%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20artificial%20general%20intelligence%20for%20machines%20that%20can%20act%20in%20the%20real%20world.%20microagi%20was%20founded%20by%20Bercan%20Kilic%20and%20Yoan%20Iliev%2C%20both%20former%20Formula%20One%20aerodynamic%20engineers%2C%20and%20Anton%20Poletaev%2C%20a%20former%20researcher%20at%20The%20Alan%20Turing%20Institute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShift%20operates%20in%2015%20countries%20and%20has%2014%2C000%20operators%20collecting%20real-world%20data%2C%20according%20to%20Kilberg.%20He%20described%20it%20as%20a%20marketplace%20%26quot%3Baimed%20at%20accelerating%20the%20transition%20from%20an%20economy%20where%20people%20work%20out%20of%20necessity%2C%20to%20one%20where%20everyday%20goods%20and%20services%20can%20become%20increasingly%20abundant%20and%20accessible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKilberg%20said%20robots%20that%20can%20reliably%20handle%20household%20chores%20are%20still%20far%20off.%20Until%20then%2C%20he%20said%2C%20people%20can%20be%20paid%20to%20gather%20the%20examples%2C%20aka%20the%20data%2C%20that%20those%20systems%20need%20to%20learn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20data%20has%20become%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20problems%20for%20startups%20and%20Big%20Tech%20companies%20trying%20to%20move%20AI%20from%20chatbots%20into%20machines%20that%20can%20act%20in%20the%20physical%20world.%20Large%20language%20models%20are%20trained%20on%20vast%20amounts%20of%20text%20and%20images%20from%20the%20internet.%20Since%20a%20comparable%20corpus%20for%20robots%20does%20not%20exist%2C%20the%20industry%20is%20trying%20to%20create%20one%20from%20scratch%20by%20paying%20gig%20workers%20to%20record%20the%20work%20robots%20may%20eventually%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20free%20cleaning%20offer%20raises%20an%20obvious%20question%3A%20Does%20the%20math%20work%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20unit%20economics%20are%20a%20lot%20better%20than%20you%20think%2C%26quot%3B%20Kilberg%20said.%20microagi's%20internal%20technology%20processes%20the%20data%20in%20a%20way%20that%20makes%20it%20significantly%20higher%20quality%2C%20allowing%20it%20to%20command%20a%20premium%20when%20sold%20to%20AI%20labs%20and%20robotics%20companies%2C%20Kilberg%20said.%20Faces%20and%20screens%20are%20automatically%20blurred%20in%20the%20videos%20to%20anonymize%20the%20data%2C%20and%20no%20audio%20is%20captured.%20microagi%20also%20uses%20the%20data%20for%20its%20own%20internal%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKilberg%20said%20the%20idea%20for%20the%20launch%20came%20from%20early%20users%20who%20were%20already%20recording%20themselves%20doing%20tasks%20around%20their%20homes%20and%20wanted%20to%20do%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20started%20putting%20up%20flyers%20in%20their%20apartment%20buildings%20offering%20cleaning%20to%20neighbors%20because%20we%20would%20foot%20the%20bill%2C%26quot%3B%20Kilberg%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20began%20stocking%20shelves%20at%20local%20bodegas%20or%20volunteering%20at%20soup%20kitchens%20while%20recording%20the%20work%2C%20he%20said.%20Kilberg%20declined%20to%20say%20how%20much%20people%20are%20paid%20to%20record%20themselves%20doing%20chores.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20York%20is%20just%20the%20beginning.%20Kilberg%20said%20Shift%20plans%20to%20expand%20across%20the%20US%20and%20add%20free%20or%20subsidized%20services%20beyond%20cleaning%2C%20including%20cooking%20and%20plumbing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShift%20is%20part%20of%20a%20growing%20market%20for%20data%20collected%20from%20the%20physical%20world.%20Scale%20AI%2C%20Turing%2C%20and%20micro1%2C%20which%20helped%20supply%20data%20for%20the%20chatbot%20boom%2C%20have%20moved%20into%20real-world%20data%20collection.%20The%20goal%20is%20to%20help%20close%20what%20UC%20Berkeley%20roboticist%20Ken%20Goldberg%20has%20called%20the%20%26quot%3B100%2C000-year%20data%20gap%26quot%3B%3A%20the%20idea%20that%20robots%20are%20far%20behind%20chatbots%20because%20they%20lack%20enough%20real-world%20training%20examples.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20more%20services%20Shift%20offers%2C%20the%20more%20useful%20its%20footage%20becomes.%20AI%20labs%20and%20robotics%20companies%20need%20training%20data%20from%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20tasks%20and%20settings%20so%20robots%20can%20learn%20from%20the%20messiness%20of%20the%20real%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShift%20is%20also%20focused%20on%20geographic%20diversity.%20Kilberg%20said%20the%20company%20operates%20in%20countries%20where%20few%20others%20are%20collecting%20this%20kind%20of%20data%2C%20including%20Bulgaria%2C%20Georgia%2C%20and%20South%20Africa.%20He%20said%20Shift%20has%20especially%20caught%20on%20in%20Turkey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthis-startup-will-clean-your-apartment-free-ai-can-watch-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780563602000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a2092aa2ab5f9757add8ee2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthis-startup-will-clean-your-apartment-free-ai-can-watch-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Shift%20Robotics%20is%20part%20of%20a%20growing%20scramble%20for%20real-world%20data%20as%20AI%20companies%20try%20to%20train%20machines%20to%20work%20in%20homes%2C%20warehouses%2C%20and%20factories.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22rjetha%40insider.com%20(Rya%20Jetha)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22CEO%20to%20staff%3A%20You're%20not%20getting%20a%20raise.%20We're%20spending%20on%20AI%20instead.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228201%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Corporate%20employee%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a1844742ab5f9757add55bb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225854%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECompanies%20are%20scrambling%20to%20find%20funds%20to%20invest%20heavily%20in%20AI%2C%20and%20some%20employees'%20benefits%20and%20pay%20are%20on%20the%20chopping%20block.%3Cp%3EEschCollection%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EStaff%20compensation%20is%20becoming%20a%20target%20for%20employers%20looking%20to%20invest%20heavily%20in%20AI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESoftware%20company%20Teradata%20told%20employees%20they%20won't%20get%20raises%20this%20year%20due%20to%20AI%20spending.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESuch%20candor%20marks%20a%20%26quot%3Bgenuinely%20new%26quot%3B%20rhetorical%20shift%2C%20a%20workplace%20strategist%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20isn't%20just%20coming%20for%20your%20job.%20It's%20coming%20for%20your%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20companies%20look%20for%20cash%20to%20fund%20their%20AI%20transformations%2C%20some%20are%20finding%20it%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-corporate-benefits-rollback-is-spreading-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eshrinking%20employee%20benefits%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20compensation%20packages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETeradata%2C%20a%20global%20cloud%20software%20company%2C%20told%20its%205%2C100%20employees%20in%20January%20not%20to%20expect%20an%20annual%20salary%20raise%20this%20year%20as%20it%20reallocates%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20budget%20toward%20AI%20investments%2C%20according%20to%20an%20internal%20memo%20seen%20by%20Business%20Insider%20and%20not%20previously%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETeradata's%20focus%20for%202026%20is%20to%20%26quot%3Bwin%20in%20the%20market%20with%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20CEO%20Steve%20McMillan%20said%20in%20the%20memo%2C%20and%20to%20help%20achieve%20that%2C%20the%20company%20will%20be%20increasing%20investment%20in%20AI%20talent%20and%20expertise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20will%20fund%20this%20AI%20investment%20by%20reallocating%20the%20budget%20from%202026%20annual%20salary%20adjustments%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20McMillan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETeradata%20did%20not%20comment%20on%20the%20budget%20decision.%20A%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20company%20is%20actively%20investing%20in%20AI%20to%20innovate%20its%20products%20and%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20US-based%20Teradata%20employees%2C%20both%20of%20whom%20have%20been%20at%20the%20company%20for%20over%2010%20years%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20they%20generally%20received%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-paying-jobs-projected-to-grow-a-lot-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannual%20salary%20increases%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%202%25%20to%204%25%2C%20though%20they%20said%20the%20increases%20were%20not%20guaranteed%20each%20year.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployees%20may%20still%20receive%20performance-based%20bonuses%20and%20equity%20shares%20as%20part%20of%20their%20compensation%2C%20the%20memo%20said.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20decision%20applies%20to%20employees%20in%20countries%20where%20regulators%20do%20not%20require%20market-aligned%20salary%20adjustments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETeradata%20is%20the%20second%20company%20that%20Business%20Insider%20has%20reported%20is%20openly%20telling%20staff%20it%20is%20pursuing%20AI%20spending%20over%20workforce%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETTEC%2C%20a%20midsize%20technology%20and%20services%20firm%2C%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fttec-pauses-401k-contributions-benefit-cuts-consulting-deloitte-zoom-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epaused%20401(k)%20matches%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20its%20US%20employees%20through%20the%20end%20of%202026%2C%20saying%20in%20internal%20communications%20that%20the%20benefits%20retreat%20would%20help%20fund%20the%20tools%2C%20training%2C%20and%20capabilities%20necessary%20for%20the%20company's%20AI%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIs%20your%20company%20cutting%20key%20benefits%20or%20pausing%20pay%20rises%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EContact%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Apthompson%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epthompson%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20Signal%20at%20Polly_Thompson.89.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%2C%20a%20nonwork%20WiFi%20network%2C%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%20here's%20our%20guide%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-guide-to-securely-sharing-whistleblower-information-about-powerful-institutions-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3Esharing%20information%20securely%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20candor%20with%20which%20leaders%20are%20naming%20AI%20as%20the%20reason%20for%20cuts%20marks%20a%20new%20rhetorical%20shift%2C%20said%20Jennifer%20Moss%2C%20a%20workplace%20strategist%20and%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BWhy%20Are%20We%20Here%3F%20Creating%20a%20Work%20Culture%20Everyone%20Wants.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhether%20that's%20more%20honest%20or%20more%20cynical%20depends%20on%20your%20read%2C%20but%20it%20does%20mark%20a%20real%20shift%20in%20what%20leaders%20are%20willing%20to%20say%20in%20public%2C%26quot%3B%20Moss%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20what%20becomes%20sayable%20tends%20to%20become%20more%20doable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224907a63d-5853-4ce3-9190-626e553ea1d4%5C%22%3EFinancing%20an%20AI%20transformation%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETTEC%20and%20Teradata%20are%20technology%20services%20companies%20operating%20in%20an%20industry%20where%20failure%20to%20adapt%20to%20AI%20is%20seen%20as%20a%20particularly%20existential%20risk.%20Across%20industries%2C%20businesses%20are%20increasing%20their%20AI%20spending.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-finally-paying-ai-cio-survey-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECIO%20survey%20from%20RBC%20Capital%3C%2Fa%3E%20polled%20117%20IT%20professionals%20at%20companies%20with%20annual%20revenues%20from%20under%20%24250%20million%20to%20more%20than%20%2425%20billion.%20It%20found%20that%2090%25%20of%20those%20surveyed%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eplanned%20to%20increase%20AI%20spending%20in%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20spending%20can%20range%20from%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20for%20small%20pilots%20or%20basic%20integrations%20to%20millions%20of%20dollars%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdell-jeff-clarke-ai-memo-biggest-transformation-in-company-history-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eenterprise-scale%20AI%20transformations%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Those%20costs%20are%20hitting%20as%20many%20companies%20are%20already%20operating%20with%20tighter%20budgets%2C%20driven%20by%20inflation%2C%20tariffs%2C%20and%20supply%20chain%20disruptions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETeradata%20and%20TTEC%20have%20both%20faced%20financial%20difficulty%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20with%20global%20revenue%20declining%205%25%20and%203.2%25%2C%20respectively%2C%20in%20each%20company's%20latest%20financial%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20AI%20costs%20may%20be%20rising%2C%20cutting%20worker%20compensation%20is%20a%20choice%2C%20not%20an%20inevitability%2C%20Moss%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETransformations%20can%20be%20financed%20through%20measures%20like%20taking%20on%20debt%2C%20reallocating%20nonessential%20spending%2C%20adjusting%20executive%20compensation%2C%20making%20acquisitions%2C%20phasing%20investments%20over%20time%2C%20or%20accepting%20lower%20margins%20for%20a%20defined%20period%2C%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlphabet%2C%20for%20example%2C%20announced%20this%20week%20that%20it%20plans%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwarren-buffett-berkshire-hathaway-cash-alphabet-ai-tech-stock-acquisition-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esell%20%2480%20billion%20in%20stock%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20fund%20its%20investments%20in%20AI%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20reason%20workforce%20compensation%20ends%20up%20being%20the%20source%20is%20that%20it's%20the%20largest%20controllable%20expense%20line%20at%20most%20companies%20and%20the%20one%20with%20the%20least%20organized%20resistance%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Moss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20actual%20cost%20of%20AI%20investment%20for%20most%20companies%20is%20relatively%20small%20compared%20to%20total%20compensation%20expense%2C%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20BCG's%202026%20AI%20Radar%2C%20a%20survey%20of%202%2C360%20global%20companies%20that%20was%20released%20in%20January%2C%20companies%20only%20expect%20to%20spend%20about%201.7%25%20of%20revenue%20on%20AI%20in%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJan-Emmanuel%20De%20Neve%2C%20an%20economist%20and%20director%20of%20Oxford%20University's%20Wellbeing%20Research%20Center%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20he%20expects%20more%20companies%20to%20make%20similar%20trade-offs%20as%20they%20pursue%20AI%2C%20saying%20it%20is%20indicative%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bshort-term%20mindset.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20leaders%20openly%20cut%20human%20compensation%20to%20fund%20AI%2C%20they%20are%20trying%20to%20project%20decisive%2C%20tech-forward%20management.%20However%2C%20the%20actual%20message%20traveling%20to%20the%20workforce%20is%20that%20they%20do%20not%20have%20a%20secure%20future%20in%20the%20organization%2C%26quot%3B%20De%20Neve%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22397beefa-fc5d-447f-b972-2f5cad34e45c%5C%22%3EEmployees%20are%20losing%20power%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECuts%20to%20benefits%20and%20salary%20adjustments%20sit%20at%20the%20gentler%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eend%20of%20the%20spectrum.%20Others%20have%20tied%20AI%20adoption%20to%20layoffs%20and%20fewer%20hiring%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%2C%20for%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fread-meta-layoff-email-employees-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elaid%20off%2010%25%20of%20its%20workforce%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20May%2C%20a%20move%20it%20linked%20to%20a%20push%20for%20efficiency%20and%20the%20need%20to%20fund%20investments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta's%20stock%20price%20has%20surged%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20and%20in%20January%2C%20the%20company%20said%20its%20capital%20spending%20for%20the%20year%20would%20range%20from%20%24115%20billion%20to%20%24135%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20firms%2C%20including%20Snap%2C%20Cisco%2C%20and%20Salesforce%2C%20have%20also%20announced%20staff%20cuts%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flist-companies-replacing-human-employees-with-ai-layoffs-workforce-reductions%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eciting%20AI%20efficiencies%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20rationale%3B%20and%20Uber%20CEO%20Dara%20Khosrowshahi%20said%20in%20May%20that%20he'll%20cover%20the%20cost%20of%20increasing%20AI%20investment%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-slowing-hiring-fund-ai-investment-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehiring%20fewer%20people%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETeradata's%20head%20count%20has%20fallen%20by%20over%2021%25%20since%20December%202023%2C%20a%20drop%20of%201%2C400%20people%20that%20the%20company%20said%20was%20made%20to%20support%20its%20growth%20strategy%2C%20company%20filings%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEllen%20Raim%2C%20an%20employment%20attorney%20with%2030%20years%20of%20corporate%20HR%20leadership%20experience%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20many%20companies%20are%20leaner%20and%20under%20increasing%20organizational%20pressure%20to%20show%20productivity%20gains%20and%20stronger%20head%20count%20ROI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAI%20is%20being%20positioned%20as%20a%20way%20to%20do%20that%20quickly%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228133%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bill%20Winters%2C%20chief%20executive%20officer%20of%20Standard%20Chartered%20Plc%2C%20during%20a%20Bloomberg%20Television%20interview%20in%20London%2C%20UK%2C%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20Feb.%2024%2C%202026.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a13f8f751ede568c7e18455%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225422%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBill%20Winters%20used%20the%20phrase%20%26quot%3Blower-value%20human%20capital%26quot%3B%20to%20refer%20to%20employees%20he%20was%20planning%20to%20lay%20off.%3Cp%3EBloomberg%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20workers%20have%20struggled%20with%20a%20perception%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-openai-doomer-boomer-pivot-ai-jobs-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20could%20lead%20to%20their%20well-being%20being%20sidelined%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20something%20recently%20reinforced%20when%20Standard%20Chartered%20CEO%20Bill%20Winters%20described%20some%20roles%20as%20%26quot%3Blower%20value%2C%20human%20capital.%26quot%3B%20Winters%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstandard-chartered-ceo-sorry-lower-value-human-capital-ai-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elater%20apologized%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Alongside%20the%20growing%20tide%20of%20layoffs%20and%20examples%20of%20AI-focused%20compensation%20cuts%20at%20TTEC%20and%20Teradata%2C%20the%20power%20balance%20is%20shifting%20against%20workers%20as%20companies%20prioritize%20their%20AI%20futures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EComments%20like%20Winters'%20reflect%20a%20broader%20trend%20of%20executives%20talking%20about%20people%20primarily%20as%20costs%20or%20capacity%2C%20Raim%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20may%20make%20sense%20on%20a%20spreadsheet%2C%20but%20it%20can%20be%20corrosive%20inside%20an%20organization.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20risk%2C%20Raim%20said%2C%20is%20that%20companies%20underinvest%20in%20employees%20and%20undermine%20trust%2C%20at%20the%20very%20time%20they%20ask%20them%20to%20embrace%20these%20new%20tools%20and%20help%20figure%20out%20where%20AI%20can%20meaningfully%20improve%20the%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteradata-pauses-raises-employee-compensation-ai-budget-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780563601000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a1844c02e5a80cfe04ffb21%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteradata-pauses-raises-employee-compensation-ai-budget-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Cloud%20software%20firm%20Teradata%20has%20told%20employees%20not%20to%20expect%20annual%20salary%20raises%20in%202026%2C%20and%20says%20it%20is%20putting%20the%20money%20towards%20AI%20instead.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22pthompson%40businessinsider.com%20(Polly%20Thompson)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Pentagon%20has%20gutted%20its%20civilian%20workforce%20under%20Trump.%20The%20cuts%20were%20haphazard%2C%20watchdog%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228256%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22US%20Secretary%20of%20Defense%20Pete%20Hegseth%20sits%20at%20a%20conference%20wearing%20a%20blue%20suit.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a2079422e5a80cfe05032d7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225504%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUnder%20the%20second%20Trump%20administration%2C%20the%20Pentagon%20has%20cut%20roughly%2010%25%20of%20its%20civilian%20workforce.%3Cp%3EJAM%20STA%20ROSA%20%2F%20AFP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20US%20Department%20of%20Defense%20hasn't%20fully%20assessed%20its%20massive%20cuts%20to%20its%20civilian%20workforce%2C%20a%20new%20report%20says.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETens%20of%20thousands%20of%20workers%20were%20rapidly%20shed%2C%20prompting%20unforeseen%20challenges%2C%20the%20GAO%20found.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20deepens%20the%20loss%20of%20institutional%20knowledge%20inside%20the%20Defense%20Department.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Pentagon%20hastily%20cut%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20its%20civilian%20workers%20last%20year.%20Its%20leaders%20didn't%20fully%20analyze%20the%20impacts%20of%20those%20reductions%20then%2C%20and%20according%20to%20a%20new%20government%20watchdog%20report%2C%20still%20haven't%20assessed%20their%20fallout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20changes%2C%20which%20included%20layoffs%2C%20resignations%2C%20and%20a%20hiring%20freeze%2C%20were%20made%20by%20the%20Trump%20administration%20amid%20a%20larger%20push%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-pentagon-asked-civilian-employees-to-submit-money-saving-ideas-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eshrink%20the%20federal%20workforce%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20the%20reductions%20produced%20some%20benefits%20for%20agencies%20inside%20the%20Pentagon%2C%20like%20automated%20workflows%20and%20savings%2C%20it%20also%20strained%20the%20remaining%20workers%20and%20diminished%20institutional%20knowledge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%2C%20released%20by%20the%20US%20Government%20Accountability%20Office%20last%20week%2C%20found%20that%20in%202025%2C%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Defense%20cut%20its%20civilian%20workforce%20by%20around%2010%25%2C%20or%20over%2078%2C000%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20DoD%20is%20required%20to%20assess%20the%20potential%20repercussions%20of%20these%20shifts%2C%20such%20as%20increased%20workload%20on%20other%20employees%20or%20costs%20saved%2C%20the%20GAO%20%26quot%3Bfound%20that%20DoD%20didn't%20consistently%20analyze%20the%20impacts%20of%20these%20reductions%2C%20either%20in%202025%20or%20in%20prior%20years.%20DoD%20also%20doesn't%20have%20a%20plan%20to%20assess%20lessons%20learned%20from%20its%202025%20workforce%20reductions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20the%2078%2C000%20workers%20that%20were%20cut%2C%20a%20hiring%20freeze%20resulted%20in%20DoD%20hiring%20about%2060%2C000%20fewer%20new%20employees%20than%20in%20previous%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20found%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20number%20of%20Pentagon%20offices%20and%20programs%20that%20are%20seeking%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-command-that-okays-military-recruits-approaching-crisis-point-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ereductions%20in%20workforce%20numbers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20jumped%20from%2010%20in%202023%2C%2011%20in%202024%2C%20and%2013%20in%202025%20to%20now%2028%20in%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227070%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20stands%20on%20the%20edge%20of%20a%20boat%20looking%20out%20at%20the%20sun%20on%20the%20horizon.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a207adf2ab5f9757add8dfd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223977%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20Pacific%20Fleet%20lost%20850%20civilian%20workers%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%20photo%20by%20Mass%20Communication%20Specialist%202nd%20Class%20Ryan%20Holloway%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%2014%20offices%20that%20the%20GAO%20selected%20for%20in-depth%20reviews%2C%20%26quot%3B11%20conducted%20some%20analysis%20of%20the%20impacts%20of%20workforce%20reductions%26quot%3B%20in%20that%20time%20period%20to%20inform%20decision-making.%20And%20of%20the%2028%20offices%20that%20cut%20workers%20because%20of%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20policies%2C%20at%20least%20three%20didn't%20give%20Congress%20explanations%20about%20why%20and%20how%20the%20decreases%20would%20be%20made.%20Those%20three%20were%20the%20Joint%20Staff%2C%20Defense%20Threat%20Reduction%20Agency%2C%20and%20Defense%20Contract%20Audit%20Agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20GAO%20also%20noted%20that%20DoD%20currently%20%26quot%3Bdoes%20not%20have%20a%20plan%20to%20assess%20lessons%20learned%20from%20these%20workforce%20reduction%20efforts.%26quot%3B%20The%20office%20recommended%20DoD%20develop%20a%20plan%20for%20this.%20The%20Pentagon%20agreed%20with%20the%20GAO's%20recommendation%20but%20didn't%20elaborate%20on%20whether%20or%20when%20that%20would%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20impacts%20of%20these%20workforce%20changes%20raise%20some%20benefits.%20Per%20the%20report%2C%20DoD%20identified%20that%20some%20offices%2C%20like%20the%20Defense%20Logistics%20Agency%2C%20automated%20some%20processes%2C%20resulting%20in%20faster%20workflows%20and%20fewer%20manual%20tasks.%20Other%20programs%20like%20the%20Defense%20Information%20Systems%20Agency%2C%20reorganized%20their%20workplaces%20to%20%26quot%3Bincrease%20efficiency%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20cases%2C%20DoD%20prompting%20voluntary%20resignations%20prevented%20offices%20and%20programs%20from%20having%20to%20make%20involuntary%20layoffs.%20There%20were%20also%20some%20signs%20of%20saved%20costs%2C%20like%20in%20the%20Defense%20Logistics%20Agency%2C%20which%20estimated%20%2412%20million%20in%20salary%20savings%20from%20government-wide%20reductions.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fproblem-with-americas-1-trillion-military-budget-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDoD's%202026%20fiscal%20year%20budget%3C%2Fa%3E%20request%20identified%20%246.8%20billion%20in%20savings%20from%20reshaping%20the%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20were%20also%20challenges.%20DLA's%20workforce%20capacity%20was%20strained%2C%20and%20there%20was%20an%20increased%20risk%20from%20high%20workload%20on%20employees%20and%20quickly%20developed%20processes%2C%20GAO%20said.%20The%20US%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkey-pacific-allys-shipyard-to-repair-us-navy-ship-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENavy's%20reductions%20delayed%20shipyard%20maintenance%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20a%20loss%20of%20experienced%20civilian%20workers%2C%20%26quot%3Bsuch%20as%20about%20850%20employees%20at%20US%20Pacific%20Fleet%2C%26quot%3B%20GAO%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20loss%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-special-forces-using-lot-of-ai-for-cognitive-load-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einstitutional%20knowledge%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20also%20an%20issue.%20US%20Space%20Force%20faces%20readiness%20problems%20because%20of%20the%20loss%20of%20civilian%20workers%2C%20the%20report%20said%2C%20and%20the%20Defense%20Information%20Systems%20Agency%20lost%20%26quot%3Bmuch%20institutional%20knowledge%20from%20reductions%20of%20roughly%2010%20percent%2C%26quot%3B%20GAO%20said.%20Similarly%2C%20because%20the%20workforce%20reductions%20weren't%20entirely%20directed%2C%20voluntary%20resignations%20pockmarked%20agencies'%20workflows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227374%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20flag%20hangs%20off%20the%20side%20of%20the%20Pentagon%20at%20dusk.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a2079dcb4fb977f35984247%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224916%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMany%20of%20the%20problems%20identified%20by%20the%20cuts%20have%20been%20long-standing%20issues%20facing%20DoD.%3Cp%3EDoD%20photo%20by%20US%20Navy%20Petty%20Officer%201st%20Class%20Eric%20Brann%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20workforce%20shifts%20have%20also%20created%20a%20perceived%20instability%20of%20government%20jobs%2C%20which%20will%20affect%20hiring%20young%20workers%20with%20desired%20skills%20in%20areas%20like%20the%20Defense%20Information%20Systems%20Agency.%20Some%20programs%20also%20noted%20that%20the%20cuts%20have%20created%20uncertainty%20in%20future%20planning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Defense%20Department%20is%20the%20largest%20federal%20employer%2C%20with%20684%2C000%20civilian%20employees%2C%20of%20whom%20over%2040%25%20are%20military%20veterans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20GAO%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20challenges%20it%20noted%20in%20its%20report%20were%20the%20strongest%20examples%20it%20found%2C%20but%20a%20total%20assessment%20of%20the%20benefits%20and%20challenges%20was%20not%20a%20main%20focus%20of%20the%20report.%20It's%20unclear%20if%20there%20are%20impacts%20or%20detriments%20because%20of%20the%20cuts%20that%20haven't%20yet%20been%20assessed%20within%20DoD.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20early%20months%20of%20the%20second%20Trump%20administration%2C%20the%20White%20House's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fread-email-doge-office-sent-federal-employees-monitor-productivity-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDepartment%20of%20Government%20Efficiency%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20DOGE%2C%20initiative%20led%20significant%20disruptions%20to%20the%20federal%20workforce%2C%20including%20civilian%20workers%20in%20the%20Pentagon.%20This%20included%20pushing%20for%20cuts%2C%20Saturday%20emails%20asking%20federal%20workers%20for%20a%20list%20of%20what%20work%20they%20accomplished%20in%20the%20previous%20week%2C%20and%20cancelling%20contracts%20across%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20challenges%20presented%20by%20the%20workforce%20shifts%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpentagon-dod-agency-cuts-layoffs-workforce-director-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elong-standing%20issues%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20organizations%20within%20DoD%20have%20faced%2C%20Dan%20Grazier%2C%20senior%20fellow%20and%20the%20director%20of%20the%20national%20security%20reform%20project%20at%20the%20Stimson%20Center%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20Grazier%20pointed%20to%20the%20example%20of%20delayed%20shipyard%20maintenance%20and%20the%20loss%20of%20civilian%20workers%20at%20Pacific%20Fleet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B850%2C%20that's%20pretty%20significant%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20but%20the%20Navy%20has%20long%20lamented%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-submarine-workers-are-leaving-for-less-demanding-jobs-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eshipyard%20maintenance%20delays%20and%20issues%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BBasically%20every%20year%2C%20the%20Navy%20and%20their%20spokespeople%20complain%20about%20shipyard%20capacity%2C%20so%20perhaps%20the%20cuts%20last%20year%20exacerbated%20that%20a%20little%20bit%2C%20but%20this%20is%20a%20long-standing%20issue%2C%20and%20Congress%20has%20repeatedly%20bestowed%20extra%20appropriations%20to%20the%20Navy%20to%20try%20to%20fix%20this%20problem%2C%20but%20then%20every%20year%20it%20gets%20worse%20anyway.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Pentagon's%20loss%20of%20institutional%20knowledge%20is%20hardly%20a%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Enew%20problem%2C%20either.%20Constant%20turnover%20across%20DoD%20means%20offices%20are%20often%20catching%20up%20on%20processes%20and%20workflows.%20Grazier%20said%20that%20if%20the%20GAO's%20documentation%20of%20these%20challenges%20amounted%20to%20the%20examples%20in%20the%20reports%2C%20it%20could%20suggest%20some%20of%20the%20changes%20didn't%20create%20new%20or%20unforeseen%20challenges%20for%20DoD%20offices%20that%20they%20weren't%20already%20facing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cuts%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpete-hegseth-signs-memo-shrink-defense-department-workforce-cuts-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPentagon's%20civilian%20workforce%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20broader%20leadership%20and%20policies%20under%20the%20Trump%20administration%20have%20led%20to%20a%20slump%20in%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ejob%20satisfaction.%20A%20survey%20conducted%20by%20the%20nonprofit%2C%20nonpartisan%20Partnership%20for%20Public%20Service%20group%2C%20released%20in%20March%2C%20showed%20drops%20across%20DoD%20in%20how%20civilian%20workers%20feel%20about%20their%20work.%20The%20biggest%20decrease%20was%20in%20the%20Navy%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarines-are-preparing-for-future-fights-but-stretched-thin-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMarine%20Corps%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20scored%20around%2036%20out%20of%20100%20in%202025%20after%20scoring%20around%2068%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpentagon-didnt-fully-assess-civilian-workforce-cuts-report-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A178